s and Growth Tools</h3>\n<h3><a title=\"Nextiva\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/nextiva/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">38. Nextiva</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Nextiva\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/nextiva/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133093\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/nextiva.png\" alt=\"nextiva wordpress plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"297\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/nextiva.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/nextiva-300x144.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Nextiva\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/nextiva/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Nextiva</a> is a VOIP business phone service that comes with unlimited free domestic calling, voicemail to email or text, advanced call routing, and more.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Call Pop provides account information, caller sentiment, and past interactions right on your screen when you get a call</li>\n<li>Sentiment Analysis lets you track customer interactions to get a complete picture of their customer journey</li>\n<li>Communicate, manage sales, and manage customers on a single screen</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Nextiva makes it easy to track and act on customer data and feedback. <a title=\"Nextiva\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/nextiva/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with Nextiva today!</a></p>\n<h3><a title=\"Referral Candy\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/referral-candy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">39. ReferralCandy</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Referral Candy\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/referral-candy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-121898\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/referralcandy-2.png\" alt=\"referralcandy - great plugin to get more referrals\" width=\"620\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/referralcandy-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/referralcandy-2-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>With <a title=\"Referral Candy\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/referral-candy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ReferralCandy</a> you can create an awesome referral program to reward loyal customers with cash, store credit, discounts, or free products for referring their friends.</p>\n<p>ReferralCandy has widgets ready to go, like a click-to-open popup, embedded sharing page, and post-purchase popup. You can also distribute awards automatically, and only successful, verified referrals are rewarded so you won&#8217;t have to worry about fake ones.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Track referral engagement, customers&#8217; shares, and new sales</li>\n<li>Cross-channel promotion to make it easy for customers to join</li>\n<li>Distribute rewards like coupons, cash, or gifts automatically</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why You Need It:</strong></p>\n<p>Referrals play an enormous role in someone&#8217;s decision to make a purchase. Think about it for a minute. If a friend or business you already trust tells you that something is worth checking out, aren&#8217;t you more likely to take a look? Referral programs let you <strong>reward your loyal customers</strong>so they know that their business and referrals mean a lot to you.</p>\n<p>These types of programs aren&#8217;t right for every business, but if you&#8217;re already getting organic word-of-mouth referrals and have 100-200 transactions per month, a referral program could be just the thing to kick your sales up a notch.</p>\n<p>Referral programs can be difficult to set up and manage, but ReferralCandy makes it easy.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Referral Candy\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/referral-candy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Click here to try ReferralCandy FREE for 30 days!</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.relevanssi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">40. Relevanssi</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.relevanssi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-121926\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/relevanssi_plugin.png\" alt=\"relevanssi_plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"371\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/relevanssi_plugin.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/relevanssi_plugin-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WordPress search isn&#8217;t the best, mostly because it doesn&#8217;t search everything. With a great plugin like <a href=\"https://www.relevanssi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Relevanssi</a>, you can customize your search to include pretty much every bit of content on your site <strong>and</strong> offer cool options like &#8220;Did you mean&#8230;&#8221; suggestions or fuzzy matching.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Extends search functionality to include comments, categories, post excerpts, and more</li>\n<li>Show &#8220;Did you mean&#8221; suggestions</li>\n<li>Multi-site support (premium)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why You Need It:</strong></p>\n<p>Visitors expect to be able to find what they need on your site. If they do a search and don&#8217;t find it quickly, they&#8217;re going to go somewhere else to find it.</p>\n<p>With the increased search functionality offered by Relevanssi, you&#8217;ll <strong>improve user experience</strong> and <strong>reduce bounce rates</strong>.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/slack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">41. Slack</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/slack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-121920\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/slack_plugin.png\" alt=\"slack_plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/slack_plugin.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/slack_plugin-300x183.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/slack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Slack</a> is great for any team, but when your team is spread out across the world like ours, it&#8217;s a must. You can use the plugin to send notifications to Slack channels when certain events in WordPress occur: a post status changes to pending, a post is published, and when there&#8217;s a new comment.</p>\n<p>This plugin also has a WooCommerce extension that lets you send a Slack notification when a payment in WooCommerce is marked as complete.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Real-time messaging between teams</li>\n<li>WordPress notifications</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why You Need It:</strong></p>\n<p>If you have a multi-author WordPress site or distributed team, Slack can keep you connected in real time.</p>\n<p>You can easily set up notifications to <strong>keep your team informed</strong> when a post is published or updated, WordPress updates are available, or if you&#8217;ve received a new comment, among several other things.</p>\n<p>The plugin also has <strong>support for WooCommerce</strong>. This means that you can automatically notify your team when you get a new order, and order is changed, or a product goes out of stock.</p>\n<p>Pushing notifications saves time and lets your team focus on the things they need to get done.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/slack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Click to sign up with Slack and get a $100 credit!</a></p>\n<h3>What to Look for in a WordPress Plugin</h3>\n<p>WordPress plugins are a great way to extend the functionality of your WordPress site. But, it&#8217;s tough to know what to look for when youre trying to choose the plugins to get the features you want without slowing down or breaking your site.</p>\n<p>Here are 3 simple things to check when looking for the best WordPress plugins:</p>\n<p><strong>1. User Reviews and Ratings</strong></p>\n<p>User reviews and ratings are an awesome place to look for information about how a plugin works in real life. Plus, reviews are generally pretty reliable and youll be able to see howor ifthe creator of the plugin responds.</p>\n<p>You can find WordPress plugin reviews and ratings in the sidebar on official plugin pages:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133649\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-reviews.png\" alt=\"wordpress plugin page reviews\" width=\"620\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-reviews.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-reviews-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>To view all the reviews simply click<strong>See all</strong> to the far right of the word<strong>Ratings</strong>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133650\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-reviews-2.png\" alt=\"see all wordpress plugin reviews\" width=\"620\" height=\"247\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-reviews-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-reviews-2-300x120.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>2. Customer Support</strong></p>\n<p>Support is another important thing to consider when choosing the best WordPress plugins for your site. Official WordPress plugins have support forums inside WordPress.org:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133651\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-support-page.png\" alt=\"wordpress plugin support page\" width=\"620\" height=\"297\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-support-page.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-support-page-300x144.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Pay attention to any pinned posts, however. Some plugin creators may maintain their own customer support outside of WordPress, as OptinMonster does.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Plugin Screenshots</strong></p>\n<p>WordPress plugin screenshots let you see what the interface looks like on both the backend and the frontend and give you an idea about what it&#8217;s like to work with the plugin. You can find the screenshots on the WordPress plugin page, towards the bottom:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133652\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-screenshots.png\" alt=\"wordpress plugins page screenshots\" width=\"620\" height=\"504\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-screenshots.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-best-wordpress-plugins-screenshots-300x244.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>There you have it! 41 of the best WordPress plugins for business to kick your business into high gear.</p>\n<p>You can&#8217;t go wrong with any of these plugins, so why not give OptinMonster a try? Get access to the BEST lead generation plugin out there <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing/\">RIGHT NOW</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-wordpress-plugins-to-grow-your-business/\">41 Best WordPress Plugins &#038; Tools of 2019 (Tested and Reviewed)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://optinmonster.com/best-wordpress-plugins-to-grow-your-business/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"40 Exit Popup Hacks That Will Grow Your Subscribers and Revenue\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://optinmonster.com/40-exit-popup-hacks-that-will-grow-your-subscribers-and-revenue/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://optinmonster.com/40-exit-popup-hacks-that-will-grow-your-subscribers-and-revenue/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 11 Jul 2019 18:45:22 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Lead Generation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"exit intent\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"exit popup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"exit-intent popup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"optin forms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"popups\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://optinmonster.com/?p=92580\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:652:\"<p>Are you looking for ways to convert more of your website visitors? Exit popups are the secret weapon that all smart marketers use to dramatically increase their conversions. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you 40 exit popup hacks that will substantially grow your subscribers, and your revenue. Exit-intent technology allows you to make one more [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/40-exit-popup-hacks-that-will-grow-your-subscribers-and-revenue/\">40 Exit Popup Hacks That Will Grow Your Subscribers and Revenue</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Jacinda Santora\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75657:\"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Sj5B3qrFnKI?rel=0\" width=\"620\" height=\"348.75\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Are you looking for ways to convert more of your website visitors? Exit popups are the secret weapon that all smart marketers use to dramatically increase their conversions. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you 40 exit popup hacks that will substantially grow your subscribers, and your revenue.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Exit Intent\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/exit-intent/\">Exit-intent technology</a> allows you to make one more effort to convert visitors as they are about to leave your site. By detecting when someone is about to navigate away, it presents the visitor with one final message (in a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/3-reasons-lightbox-popups-capture-more-emails/\">lightbox popup overlay</a>) right at that pivotal moment.</p>\n<p>Unlike immediate popups, which interrupt your visitor as they&#8217;re trying to browse your site, exit popups aren&#8217;t an annoyance.</p>\n<p>Now, some people are of the opinion that <strong>any</strong> form of <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/6-reasons-pop-ups-welcome-gates-and-slide-ins-suck-and-the-solution/\">popup is an annoyance</a>. However, even if your exit popup does annoy the occasional visitor, they were about to head out anyway. There&#8217;s no harm in trying to get there attention before they&#8217;ve got the door closed.</p>\n<p>The truth is, <strong>regardless of how you feel about popups</strong>, data shows that exit popups actually do work really well. When you implement an exit-intent popup on your site, you could <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/case-study-fastrack-recovers-53-percent-of-abandoning-visitors/\"><strong>recover 53% of abandoning visitors</strong></a> like OptinMonster customer Fastrack.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-122344\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Fastrack-Group-Exit-Intent-Optin.jpg\" alt=\"Fastrack Group Exit-Intent popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"410\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Fastrack-Group-Exit-Intent-Optin.jpg 1180w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Fastrack-Group-Exit-Intent-Optin-300x198.jpg 300w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Fastrack-Group-Exit-Intent-Optin-768x508.jpg 768w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Fastrack-Group-Exit-Intent-Optin-1024x677.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>We can&#8217;t guarantee that your results will be quite that dramatic, but if you&#8217;re not using exit popups, you&#8217;re leaving a lot of money on the table.</p>\n<p>So, without further ado, whether you&#8217;re looking for an idea for your very first exit popup, or looking for new things to tweak and test, here are 40 exit popup hacks to get you started:</p>\n<h3>1. Use Your Visitor&#8217;s Name</h3>\n<p>The big reason that so many popups are aggravating to users isn&#8217;t that they&#8217;re advertisementsit&#8217;s because they&#8217;re usually far too generic. Personalization can make all the difference, which is why it starts out our list of exit popup hacks.</p>\n<p>Imagine moving into a new neighborhood. You head down to the store on the corner and end up chatting with the owner for half an hour about your shared love of breakfast burritos.</p>\n<p>As you&#8217;re walking by a few days later, one of the street vendors yells out at you, encouraging you to buy an apple from their cart. Then, you hear your name; it&#8217;s the shop owner you met the other day, smiling at you and inviting you into their shop.</p>\n<p>Are you going to buy an apple from an anonymous vendor or the shop owner calling to you by name and smiling at you warmly?</p>\n<p>Yeah, we&#8217;d pick the shop owner, too.</p>\n<p>Guess what? Your website can do the same thing.</p>\n<p>Before you ever ask for a sale, ask your visitor for their name.</p>\n<p>Later, when your visitor is about to abandon one of your product pages, you could grab their attention with an exit popup with their own name on it:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-133634 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/optinmonster-smart-tags-example.png\" alt=\"exit popup hacks personalization example\" width=\"620\" height=\"510\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/optinmonster-smart-tags-example.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/optinmonster-smart-tags-example-300x247.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">Personalize your exit popups with the visitor&#8217;s name, or any variable you want, using <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-to-use-smart-tags-in-optinmonster/\">OptinMonster&#8217;s Smart Tags</a>.</div>\n<p>You can do this by getting your visitor&#8217;s name when they subscribe to your email list, by asking for their name in a previous popup, or by detecting the name of an existing customer.</p>\n<h3>2. Personalize by Referral Source</h3>\n<p>Continuing in our list of exit popup hacks, in the coveted number 2 spot, is yet another personalization tip. As we just discussed, personalization is key to making advertisements like exit popups feel more friendly.</p>\n<p>One super smart and simple way to do that is by personalizing the popup based on the referral source.</p>\n<p>For example, let&#8217;s say the visitor got to your page through a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/6-guest-blogging-mistakes-that-are-costing-you-thousands-of-subscribers/\">guest post you wrote</a> for a specific website. Or perhaps you got featured somewhere recently, and you want to get the most out of that traffic by personalizing your exit popups for that particular audience.</p>\n<p>You can use <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-to-use-optinmonster-referral-detection/\">referrer detection technology</a> to detect when a visitor is coming from any specific domain, and use that information to customize your exit popups.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example from <a href=\"http://rebootauthentic.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">RebootAuthentic</a>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94964 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Welcome-Smart-Blogger-Readers.png\" alt=\"exit popup hacks referral traffic example\" width=\"620\" height=\"539\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Welcome-Smart-Blogger-Readers.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Welcome-Smart-Blogger-Readers-300x261.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>See how the headline is personalized for Smart Blogger readers? You can personalize your exit popups for any audience you choose.</p>\n<p>Another possibility is to personalize your popups for traffic coming from your social media channels. For example, if the referring domain is Pinterest, your exit popup could include an offer that appeals to those visitors.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-121137\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/referral_site_popup_pinterest.png\" alt=\"referral_site_popup_pinterest\" width=\"620\" height=\"309\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/referral_site_popup_pinterest.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/referral_site_popup_pinterest-300x150.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If the referring domain is Facebook, you could invite visitors to join the conversation over on your Facebook page or private Facebook group.</p>\n<p>Think like a detective: what information can you deduce about your visitors from the referring domain? How can you use that knowledge to personalize your exit popup?</p>\n<h3>3. Offer a Content Upgrade</h3>\n<p>How about presenting your abandoning visitor with an upgrade to the content they were just reading?</p>\n<p>By offering content upgrades, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-razorsocial-increased-conversions-by-520-using-content-upgrades/\">RazorSocial <strong>increased their conversions by a whopping 520%</strong></a>!</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-93320\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/razorsocial_optin-e1460657491626.png\" alt=\"RazorSocial Exit Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"342\" /></p>\n<p>A <a title=\"30 Content Upgrade Ideas to Grow Your Email List\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/30-content-upgrade-ideas-to-grow-your-email-list/\">content upgrade</a> is simply a more in-depth or a higher-value version of a particular blog post. So for example, let&#8217;s say your blog post is about <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-an-email-newsletter/\">how to create an email newsletter</a>. Your visitors might read the post and be very interested in getting started, but think that they don&#8217;t have time right now.</p>\n<p>As they go to close the browser, present them with a free download of a downloadable PDF version of the post or a checklist with the steps they need to follow.</p>\n<p>If you need some help creating your content upgrades, check out these <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/10-tools-to-help-you-create-quality-content-upgrades/\">10 tools to help you create quality content upgrades</a>.</p>\n<h3>4. Suggest Related Posts</h3>\n<p>Your website is your online storefront and the longer someone stays in your store, the better. So, sometimes your main objective is simply to reduce your bounce rate and have your visitors spend more time on your site.</p>\n<p>A really great way to do that is by using an exit-intent popup to suggest blog posts that are related to the one they were just reading.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94966\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd;\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Related-Posts.png\" alt=\"Related Posts\" width=\"620\" height=\"305\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Related-Posts.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Related-Posts-300x148.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Remember, there are a number of different reasons why someone might be about to click away from your site, and it doesn&#8217;t always mean that they aren&#8217;t enjoying your content. Perhaps they simply got distracted by something, like a new email or social media notification.</p>\n<p>Remind them why they visited your site in the first place: to get specific information from your content.</p>\n<p>The key to the related posts technique is making sure that your headlines are highly clickable. Also, use enticing images that draw the eye and relate specifically to the post topic. If your related posts are appealing, you&#8217;re more likely to re-engage distracted visitors and persuade them to stick around for a while longer.</p>\n<h3>5. Give Visitors a Few Choices</h3>\n<p>The problem with so many exit popups is that they don&#8217;t offer something the visitor really wants. This happens because many businesses have several different <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/6-effective-ways-to-tailor-your-content-to-your-buyer-persona/\">buyer personas</a>, and each persona is going to respond to offers differently.</p>\n<p>Sure, your popup might be offering the greatest ebook known to man about how to juggle 6 balls in the air, but if a segment of your visitors has already mastered that technique, and now wants to learn how to spin a ball on their nose, then your offer is useless for capturing those visitors.</p>\n<p>A simple way to get around this problem and present the perfect offer to each visitor is by letting them choose what they&#8217;re most interested in.</p>\n<p>You can do it like this: first, present an exit-popup with 2-3 options for them to choose from.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95886\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Multiple-Choice-Popup.jpg\" alt=\"Multiple-Choice-Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Multiple-Choice-Popup.jpg 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Multiple-Choice-Popup-300x194.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once they select an option, present them with the optin form to get a lead magnet specifically tailored to the topic they chose.</p>\n<h3>6. Add a Progress Bar</h3>\n<p>There is a psychological phenomenon that makes people feel uncomfortable leaving things incomplete. It&#8217;s known as the <a href=\"https://medium.com/psychology-secrets-for-marketing/zeigarnik-effect-698a7e8e7353#.o3f14x42t\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Zeigarnik Effect</a>, a term coined by the 20th-century Russian psychologist, Bluma Zeigarnik.</p>\n<p>Zeigarnik saw that waiters could remember long food orders and match the correct meal to each customer but they promptly forgot these orders as soon as the food was delivered. She wondered why, so she conducted a <a href=\"http://codeblab.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/On-Finished-and-Unfinished-Tasks.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">series of experiments</a> to figure it out.</p>\n<p>Her theory was that the pending order created a state of &#8220;incompleteness&#8221; in the waiter&#8217;s mind, which made them unable to let go of the information until that state of mind was resolved through delivery of the meal.</p>\n<p>Through her experiments, Zeigarnik discovered that unfinished tasks are remembered about twice as well as completed ones and that we as humans have a child-like impatience to gratify this need for closure.</p>\n<p>You can take advantage of the Zeigarnik Effect to coax your visitors into action by showing them that they have an incomplete task. By pointing out the &#8220;incompleteness,&#8221; they&#8217;ll seek to get closure by completing the task.</p>\n<p>LinkedIn does this by showing you your progress as you fill out your profile. By showing you your &#8220;profile completeness,&#8221; you get the urge to enter all the information that they want until your profile appears as &#8220;100% complete.&#8221;</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95140\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/LinkedIn-Profile-Completeness.png\" alt=\"LinkedIn Profile Completeness\" width=\"388\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/LinkedIn-Profile-Completeness.png 388w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/LinkedIn-Profile-Completeness-300x255.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 388px) 100vw, 388px\" /></p>\n<p>This can work for exit popups as well. All you have to do is display a progress bar at the top. Here&#8217;s an example from <a href=\"http://coschedule.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">CoSchedule</a>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94982\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd;\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/coschedule-popup.gif\" alt=\"coschedule popup\" width=\"621\" height=\"341\" /></p>\n<h3>7. Include a Picture of the Bribe</h3>\n<p>Images can make a huge difference in any online marketing campaign, and exit popups are no exception.</p>\n<p>In eCommerce, <strong>67% of consumers</strong> say that the quality of the product image is &#8220;very important&#8221; in selecting and purchasing the productmore important than product-specific information, a long description, or even ratings and reviews!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mdgadvertising.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/its-all-about-images-infographic_1000.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-95142 aligncenter\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/All-About-Images-Infographic-e1460718351413.png\" alt=\"All About Images Infographic\" width=\"619\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/All-About-Images-Infographic-e1460718351413.png 619w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/All-About-Images-Infographic-e1460718351413-300x195.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 619px) 100vw, 619px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Images are so important to shoppers when deciding whether to purchase a product, so think about how you could use images to get people to do something smaller, like entering their email address for your free ebook.</p>\n<p>Matthew Barby includes an appealing mockup of his Growth Hacking eBook in his popup:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95145\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/growth-hacking-ebook-popup-e1460718990243.png\" alt=\"Matthew Barby popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"396\" /></p>\n<p>Since he&#8217;s using an image of the product, which includes its title, he doesn&#8217;t even need that much copy to get the point across. The only description he really includes (or needs) is that the book you&#8217;ll get is 54 pages long.</p>\n<p>If Barby removed the image, it might be a whole lot less appealing, right?</p>\n<h3>8. Overcome Objections</h3>\n<p>This is one of the best exit popup hacks for eCommerce <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/18-ingredients-of-high-converting-product-pages/\">product pages</a> and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-checkout-page-optimization/\">checkout pages</a>.</p>\n<p>What if your potential customer is on the fence about purchasing your product because of just one small objection, and if you could overcome that objection it would be the last nudge they need to make the purchase?</p>\n<p>One of the biggest objections that shoppers have is the worry that they will buy your product and later regret it. The dreaded Buyer&#8217;s Remorse.</p>\n<p>Thankfully, this is also one of the easiest objections to overcome when you provide some sort of money back guarantee.</p>\n<p>Neil Patel overcomes this objection by including a 30-day money back guarantee on his exit popup for <a href=\"https://www.quicksprout.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Quick Sprout</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94975\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Quick-Sprout-Traffic-University-SEO-and-Online-Marketing-Training-e1460607342164.png\" alt=\"Overcome Objections\" width=\"620\" height=\"267\" /></p>\n<p>But don&#8217;t stop at a money back guarantee. Take inventory of all the likely objections that your shoppers may have, and check that you&#8217;ve thoroughly covered them all, either on your product or checkout page or on your exit popup.</p>\n<p>Here are the <strong>10 most common objections</strong> that online shoppers have, and ideas for how you can overcome those objections in your exit popup:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>I need to think about it.</strong>People make purchases based on emotion, so if you appeal to them on an emotional level, you&#8217;ll likely overcome this objection.</li>\n<li><strong>I need to talk to my wife/husband/partner.</strong> Give them a reason why their significant other will be grateful that they got this product.</li>\n<li><strong>I can find it cheaper somewhere else.</strong>Demonstrate that you&#8217;re the best value or the best price around.</li>\n<li><strong>I&#8217;m happy with what I already have.</strong>Show them how their life will be better with your product.</li>\n<li><strong>I don&#8217;t have the budget.</strong>Offer a payment plan. Or, calculate how your product will actually save them money, or make them money in the long run.</li>\n<li><strong>I&#8217;m not sure if it will work for me.</strong>Offer a trial.</li>\n<li><strong>How do I know my credit card information will be safe?</strong>Display a security badge.</li>\n<li><strong>I don&#8217;t have time right now.</strong>Throw in a limited-time bonus.</li>\n<li><strong>Why should I choose you instead of the other guy?</strong>Show what makes you better than your competitors.</li>\n<li><strong>I&#8217;m not sure it has all the features I need.</strong>Highlight your most amazing features in a bulleted list.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>9. Give a Reminder</h3>\n<p>When a shopper is about to abandon their cart, do you use an exit-intent popup to recover them?</p>\n<p>Exit popup hacks #6 and #9 both use the Zeigarnik effect to prevent <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-advanced-tips-to-reduce-shopping-cart-abandonment/\">shopping cart abandonment</a>.</p>\n<p>Simply remind them that they still have items left in their cart, and it will create a strongsometimes irresistibleurge to get closure by completing the purchase.</p>\n<p>Your copy could say something along the lines of, &#8220;Wait! You still have these items in your cart&#8230;&#8221; or &#8220;Wait! Don&#8217;t leave without your&#8230;&#8221; and then show images of the items they are about to leave behind.</p>\n<p>Sometimes, however, shoppers just aren&#8217;t ready to buy, even though they&#8217;re still interested. Offer to save their basket, and collect their email in the process. Then it will be super easy for them to come back to your site and pick up where they left off, and you can even <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-an-abandoned-cart-email-strategy/\">start sending them emails</a>. Check out our list of <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/abandoned-cart-email-examples/\">abandoned cart email examples</a> for inspiration.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-95151\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-Cart-to-Email.png\" alt=\"Save Cart to Email\" width=\"620\" height=\"429\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-Cart-to-Email.png 578w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-Cart-to-Email-300x208.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>10. Offer a Discount</h3>\n<p>The great thing about offering a discount in an exit popup, in exchange for the visitor&#8217;s email address, is that it accomplishes two things at once:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Offering a discount encourages shoppers to go through with a purchase they were on the fence about.</li>\n<li>Even if they don&#8217;t buy today, offering a coupon rarely fails to at least collect their email address, so you can market to them in the future.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example:</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-95169 aligncenter\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Email-for-Discount-e1460755038623.png\" alt=\"Email for Discount\" width=\"620\" height=\"400\" /></p>\n<p>What&#8217;s really great about this example is that they also point out that getting on the email list gives you exclusive access to new products and discountseven more reason to opt in! And instead of a generic &#8220;Subscribe&#8221; button, they&#8217;ve used much more compelling copy, &#8220;Get My Discount Now.&#8221;</p>\n<p>If you are looking for a surefire way to recover visitors who are about to abandon your eCommerce site, coupon exit popups are the way to do it. After all, if someone is interested in buying your products, why wouldn&#8217;t they accept an easy discount?</p>\n<p><strong>Pro Tip</strong>: Make sure to include any fine print about the offer somewhere at the bottom of your exit popup.</p>\n<h3>11. Offer Free Shipping</h3>\n<p>Did you know that shipping costs are the #1 reason for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-advanced-tips-to-reduce-shopping-cart-abandonment/\">shopping cart abandonment</a>? Offer free shipping in your exit popup, and you stand to recover <strong>44% of shoppers</strong> about to abandon their carts.</p>\n<p>So, free shipping exit popups are a no-brainer. However, there are two different ways you can approach them.</p>\n<p>The first way is to give the free shipping coupon code right inside the exit popup, as shown below:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-92999\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Free-Shipping-Over-50.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Free-Shipping-Over-50.jpg 695w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Free-Shipping-Over-50-300x173.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>To make the purchase easier, you might even include a link back to the product they were viewing, or a link back to the shopping cart, similar to what <a href=\"http://babyage.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Baby Age</a> does below with their &#8220;Apply Coupon Instantly&#8221; button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95166\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Apply-Coupon-Instantly-e1460754308554.png\" alt=\"Apply Coupon Instantly\" width=\"620\" height=\"400\" /></p>\n<p>The advantage of this method is that there&#8217;s no additional work needed on the shopper&#8217;s part to complete their purchase. If they were already thinking about buying, but shipping was an issue, all they need to do is copy and paste the coupon code and checkout.</p>\n<p>The only disadvantage to this method is if they don&#8217;t buy now, you&#8217;ll have missed out on collecting their email address.</p>\n<p>We suggest giving the free shipping code directly on your <strong>shopping cart pages</strong> to prevent shopping cart abandonment. On product pages, you might try offering the free shipping in exchange for an email address.</p>\n<p>As with anything, you&#8217;ll need to test it out to see what creates the best results for you.</p>\n<h3>12. Create Scarcity</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s a well-known fact that <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/scarcity-examples-to-boost-your-conversions/\">scarcity</a> (having less of something) increases the urge to buy. Nobody wants to miss out on getting something they want, and it doesn&#8217;t feel good when someone else gets it and you don&#8217;t.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.zulily.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Zulily</a> does an amazing job of creating scarcity. When you add an item to your cart, they include the number of items left (e.g. &#8220;HURRYonly 6 left!&#8221;) in big red letters on the shopping cart page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95172\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd;\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Zulilly-Scarcity.png\" alt=\"Zulilly Scarcity\" width=\"620\" height=\"203\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Zulilly-Scarcity.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Zulilly-Scarcity-300x98.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Now imagine how effective this could be as an exit popup that appears when someone is about to abandon their cart.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.booking.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Booking.com</a> uses a popup during the reservation process to show how many other people are looking at the same hotel. Better act now before someone else gets your room!</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95174\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/booking-scarcity-popup-e1460756491465.png\" alt=\"booking scarcity popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"235\" /></p>\n<h3>13. Add Urgency</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s human nature to procrastinate. Whether it&#8217;s deciding to enter an email address or make a large purchase, people tend to avoid making difficult decisions.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-use-urgency-to-hack-your-conversion-rate/\">Urgency</a> gets the ball rolling by defining a definite deadline, either you get the offer before this time, or you miss out.</p>\n<p>OptinMonster&#8217;s exit popup highlights the limited time discount with yellow and a red arrow so you are sure to notice it.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-90398\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/urgencycouponpopup.png\" alt=\"Urgency Coupon Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"508\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/urgencycouponpopup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/urgencycouponpopup-300x246.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.diamondcandles.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Diamond Candles</a> uses a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/create-countdown-timer-optin/\">countdown timer</a> to just a few minutes, so you have to check out right now or you&#8217;ll miss out on the free shipping.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95167\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Popup-with-Timer-e1460754417300.png\" alt=\"Popup with Timer\" width=\"620\" height=\"409\" /></p>\n<h3>14. Offer a Free Trial</h3>\n<p>It takes approximately 7 touches to make a sale, so offering a free trial gives you a great chance to get your foot in the door and warm up your leads with multiple touches.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.snacknation.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Snack Nation</a> understands this well. All you have to do to get a free sample box delivered to you is cover the $9.95 shipping and handling.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-92986 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/freetrial_snacknation.png\" alt=\"Snack Nation Exit Popup\" width=\"638\" height=\"501\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/freetrial_snacknation.png 638w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/freetrial_snacknation-300x236.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 638px) 100vw, 638px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.webdesignerdepot.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Web Designer Depot</a> offers 7 days of free downloads. What&#8217;s great about this popup is they bring to your attention how valuable these 7 days are, with over 250,000 graphics, icons, vectors and more.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95000\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/WebDesignerDepot.jpg\" alt=\"WebDesignerDepot\" width=\"580\" height=\"459\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/WebDesignerDepot.jpg 580w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/WebDesignerDepot-300x237.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></p>\n<h3>15. Suggest Related Products</h3>\n<p>Similar to suggesting related posts in an exit popup on a blog post page (as in exit popup hack #4), you can also suggest related products on product pages.</p>\n<p>If you have a wide range of products (like clothing or shoes), it&#8217;s extremely helpful to recommend other similar products related to the one that the shopper is viewing. The product that they&#8217;re looking at might not be the right fit, but a similar product might be just what they need.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-92993\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/relatedproductpopup.png\" alt=\"relatedproductpopup\" width=\"620\" height=\"455\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/relatedproductpopup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/relatedproductpopup-300x220.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>16. Suggest Popular Products</h3>\n<p>Throw some <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-ways-to-use-social-proof-to-increase-your-conversions/\">social proof</a> into the mix and suggest your most popular items in an exit popup.</p>\n<p>Not only does this help keep shoppers on your eCommerce site for longer, but it reminds them that other shoppers love your products too!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://muubaa.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Muubbaa</a> uses the headline, &#8220;Most Wanted&#8221; to reinforce the desirability of their clothing.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94941\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Muubaa-Popup.png\" alt=\"Muubaa Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Muubaa-Popup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Muubaa-Popup-300x205.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>17. Offer More Value</h3>\n<p>Some customers might be leaving because the product you offered wasn&#8217;t quite robust enough for them. If you think that might be the case, offer them an upgraded version of your product (known as an <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/upselling-tips-and-examples/\">upsell</a>).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ncl.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Norwegian Cruise Line</a> adds value by offering additional amenities to your reservation, free of charge.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-92988\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/upgrade_norwegian.png\" alt=\"upgrade_norwegian\" width=\"621\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/upgrade_norwegian.png 640w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/upgrade_norwegian-300x201.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px\" /></p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t hold anything back that you can offer or give away as a bonus. Your exit popup is your last chance to capture those leads, so make it good!</p>\n<h3>18. Present a Survey</h3>\n<p>Surveys are a great way to learn more about your visitors and how you can make your website better. However, many sites use them at the wrong times, which makes for terrible user experience.</p>\n<p>Imagine landing on a website for the first time and then being hit with a survey about how your experience has been on the website. Or being right in the middle of a purchase, and getting interrupted by a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-wordpress-popup/\">popup survey</a>. That would be pretty annoying, right?</p>\n<p>The good thing about exit popups is that they don&#8217;t interrupt you in the middle of doing something on the page. This makes exit popups great for surveys. Just make sure that you don&#8217;t include a survey on your homepage, or on any other page that wouldn&#8217;t make sense for someone to be filling out your survey.</p>\n<p>Also, be respectful of your visitor&#8217;s time and don&#8217;t expect them to fill out a survey for nothing. Give them something in exchange. Here&#8217;s an example of a quick 15-second survey with a free gift:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95228\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/surveypopup.png\" alt=\"Survey Exit Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"455\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/surveypopup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/surveypopup-300x220.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>19. Give a Quiz</h3>\n<p>Quizzes are one of the most irresistible lead magnets because they provide personalized information based on how the user responds. Personality type quizzes are especially popular.</p>\n<p>Why? <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/05/psychology-online-quiz_n_4725593.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Robert Simmermon, Ph.D.</a>, a media psychologist, says, &#8220;I think [online quizzes] are fun, but I think it also does touch something about our own sense of our unfolding story.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Quizzes satisfy our natural desire to make sense of our lives by organizing events into stories to create our own biographies (according to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Narrative_psychology\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">narrative psychology</a>). They also offer the opportunity to reaffirm judgments we&#8217;ve already made about ourselves, and let us be the heroes of our own story.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.visualdna.com/quizzes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">VisualDNA</a> uses quizzes to gather insights into audiences. People voluntarily take their quizzes to uncover who they are on the basis of psychological theory, and they get to amass an enormous amount of audience data. It&#8217;s brilliant!</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95230\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Who-am-I-Quiz.png\" alt=\"Who am I Quiz\" width=\"551\" height=\"323\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Who-am-I-Quiz.png 551w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Who-am-I-Quiz-300x176.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 551px) 100vw, 551px\" /></p>\n<p>But quizzes aren&#8217;t just limited to personality types. You can use quizzes to re-engage your abandoning visitors on just about any topic.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example of an exit popup quiz from <a href=\"http://www.healingaddcourse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Healing ADD</a> on finding your ADD type:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94939\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ADD-Quiz-e1460868411426.jpg\" alt=\"ADD Quiz Popup\" width=\"533\" height=\"317\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ADD-Quiz-e1460868411426.jpg 533w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ADD-Quiz-e1460868411426-300x178.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 533px) 100vw, 533px\" /></p>\n<h3>20. Offer a Done-for-You</h3>\n<p>Sometimes your visitor is enjoying your content, but they&#8217;re too busy to implement your advice on their own. Solve that problem for your visitors by offering a done-for-you solution.</p>\n<p>For example, <a href=\"http://www.bettymeansbusiness.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Betty Means Business</a> offers 3 essential done-for-you scripts to attract more clients.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94971\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/BettyMeansBusiness-e1460909810803.jpg\" alt=\"Betty Means Business\" width=\"600\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/BettyMeansBusiness-e1460909810803.jpg 600w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/BettyMeansBusiness-e1460909810803-300x194.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>You could offer something similar with a fill-in-the-blank PDF template, an Excel spreadsheet, a Photoshop file, a Word Document, or even audio clips.</p>\n<p>On product pages, you could implement an exit popup with an offer to configure the product for the customer. Or, if the product requires any work on the customer&#8217;s part, offer a complete done-for-you service.</p>\n<p>Put yourself in your visitor&#8217;s shoes and think, &#8220;What can I do to make their life easier?&#8221; If you can save them from a lot of time or frustration, you&#8217;ll have the perfect hook for your exit popup.</p>\n<h3>21. Use the Word, &#8220;Wait&#8221;</h3>\n<p>Stop your visitors in their tracks with the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/700-power-words-that-will-boost-your-conversions/\">powerful word</a>, &#8220;wait.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Perhaps it&#8217;s due to our need for closure, but there&#8217;s something alluring about the word &#8220;wait,&#8221; isn&#8217;t there? What are you waiting for? So mysterious!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.buymustard.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Green Mountain Mustard</a> knows you were thinking about buying mustard since you were browsing their site, so their exit popup gives you a friendly reminder.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94973\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Wait-you-forgot-your-mustard-e1460607164736.png\" alt=\"Wait you forgot your mustard\" width=\"620\" height=\"396\" /></p>\n<p>You could do the same thing on a landing page or a product page. Remind visitors of what they&#8217;ll miss out on if they click away now.</p>\n<h3>22. Make Them Laugh</h3>\n<p>Another reason visitors bail on your site is that they&#8217;re simply bored. But if you can make them smile or even laugh, it will be hard for them not to take you up on your parting offer.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://klientboost.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">KlientBoost</a> uses the &#8220;pile of poo&#8221; emojithose cute, smiling piles of poopto lighten the mood.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-92901\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/klientboost_casualoptin.png\" alt=\"klientboost_casualoptin\" width=\"620\" height=\"389\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/klientboost_casualoptin.png 806w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/klientboost_casualoptin-300x188.png 300w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/klientboost_casualoptin-768x482.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s another example of a humorous exit popup. How can you resist those big, brown puppy eyes?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://blog.storeya.com/2014/07/getting-creative-exit-pop/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-95238\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd;\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Please-dont-go-exit-popup.png\" alt=\"Please don\'t go exit popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"509\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Please-dont-go-exit-popup.png 559w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Please-dont-go-exit-popup-300x246.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.gq.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GQ Magazine</a> gets real in-your-face with this humorous exit popup:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95239\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/GQ-pop-up-exit-intent-e1460912776289.png\" alt=\"GQ pop up exit intent\" width=\"588\" height=\"359\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/GQ-pop-up-exit-intent-e1460912776289.png 588w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/GQ-pop-up-exit-intent-e1460912776289-300x183.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 588px) 100vw, 588px\" /></p>\n<p>If humor fits with your brand, this is not the time to hold it in, so let it loose in your exit popup!</p>\n<h3>23. Offer to Chat</h3>\n<p>You&#8217;ve probably been on a sales page before where you saw a chat box pop up, like this one from <a href=\"https://www.xhtmlchop.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Xchop</a>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95003\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/XHTML-Chop.png\" alt=\"XHTML Chop\" width=\"620\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/XHTML-Chop.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/XHTML-Chop-300x195.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>This, of course, lets you give your potential customers answers to any questions they may have about purchasing your product or service.</p>\n<p>However, you don&#8217;t have to offer 24-hour live chat in order to be helpful to your visitors.</p>\n<p>Use your exit-intent popup to schedule a time to chat at a later date. <a href=\"http://neilpatel.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Neil Patel</a> asks for the visitor&#8217;s name, email and website URL to reserve a confidential discussion:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94972\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Neil-Patel-popup-e1460913428274.png\" alt=\"Neil Patel popup\" width=\"594\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Neil-Patel-popup-e1460913428274.png 594w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Neil-Patel-popup-e1460913428274-300x196.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\" /></p>\n<p>And here&#8217;s another example where the popup asks for the best contact information, giving the choice of either email or phone:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://timesulin.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94943 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Answer-Questions-Popup-e1460590754422.png\" alt=\"Answer Questions Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"385\" /></a></p>\n<h3>24. Use a 2-Step Optin</h3>\n<p>Psychologists have discovered that we all have a <a href=\"http://www.emailmonday.com/harnessing-the-mental-momentum-online-marketing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">strong urge to be consistent</a>. Once we make a decision or perform an action, we have the tendency to stick by that decision in all our future actions. This is known as a &#8220;decision heuristic:&#8221; a mental shortcut for making decisions.</p>\n<p>Asking your visitors to take the first step is always the hardest. But if they just take that one step, all the next steps will become much easier. That&#8217;s because they are building up mental momentum.</p>\n<p>Making that first step reallyeasy for prospects to take gets the ball rolling. Then, you can get them to take a more difficult action. Kind of like a domino effect, you have to apply a bit of force to knock down the first domino but after that, all the other dominos fall down effortlessly.</p>\n<p>Smart marketers understand this principle and put it to use in their optin forms by asking for an easy action first (press a button) before asking for a more difficult action (submitting their email address). This is called a 2-step opt-in.</p>\n<p>How can you use a 2-step opt-in with your exit popups? Simple. Place a button on the exit popup that users will have to click before they can see the opt-in form. Use a call-to-action that would be a no-brainer for your target subscriber or something they simply can&#8217;t resist.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.matthewbarby.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-95292 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Two-Step-Popup.png\" alt=\"Two Step Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"405\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Two-Step-Popup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Two-Step-Popup-300x196.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>For example, <a href=\"https://www.quicksprout.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">QuickSprout</a> once used the headline, &#8220;Are You Doing Your SEO Wrong?&#8221; If this headline had been on a 2-step exit popup, they could have had a button below it saying, &#8220;Click Here to Find Out.&#8221; Then after the click, they could have displayed the opt-in form.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://teamtreehouse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Treehouse</a> uses the headline, &#8220;Change your Career. Change your Life.&#8221; If they put that headline on a 2-step exit popup, they could display a button below it saying, &#8220;Claim Your Free Trial.&#8221; Then, they reveal the form to enter your name and email.</p>\n<p>See how that works? A simple button looks a lot more harmless than a form asking for information. Visitors won&#8217;t see the harm in taking that first action, but then they&#8217;ll feel committed to following through.</p>\n<h3>25. Give a Yes/No Choice</h3>\n<p>Another version of the 2-step opt-in is a yes/no choice. But instead of just one call to action button, you offer two: a &#8220;right&#8221; choice and a &#8220;wrong&#8221; choice.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example from <a href=\"http://socialtriggers.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Social Triggers</a>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-92903\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd;\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/SocialTriggers-YesNO-e1456160858571.jpg\" alt=\"SocialTriggers-YesNO\" width=\"620\" height=\"537\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/SocialTriggers-YesNO-e1456160858571.jpg 650w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/SocialTriggers-YesNO-e1456160858571-300x260.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\"><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-to-create-a-yes-no-optin-with-optinmonster/\">Learn how easy it is to create a Yes/No exit popup with OptinMonster!</a></div>\n<p>This works to increase conversions because of the <a href=\"http://blog.motivemetrics.com/Psychology-of-Choice-How-We-Assess-Risk-When-Buying-Products\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">psychology of choice</a>: when given a choice of doing something, people are more likely to want to do that very thing.</p>\n<p>Choices make us feel more in control, more powerful. When we feel powerful, we tend to act more impulsively when it comes to making decisions.</p>\n<p>For this to work for your exit popup, you need to make the &#8220;right&#8221; choice really obvious to the visitor. So obvious, in fact, that they don&#8217;t even have to think. Remember, the minute they have to think about the choice, you&#8217;ve lost them.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/which-color-button-converts-best/\">color of your call to action buttons</a> is important for this type of exit popup. We&#8217;ve been conditioned to associate bold colors with action, and dull colors with inaction. By making one button pop with a bright red color, and making the other button grayed out, the visitor gets the psychological message that they&#8217;re supposed to click on the red button and not the gray one.</p>\n<p>Be sure to use your powers for good and not evil.<img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f609.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>Your button copy is important too. You want your users to feel that they actually have a choice while still making it a no-brainer decision. This is something of an art, and many marketers tend to go over the line by writing copy that sounds too pushy or condescending.</p>\n<p>The Social Triggers example above is a great example because the negative option uses the word, &#8220;reject.&#8221; This is an excellent word to use because it&#8217;s empowering. Being able to reject something gives me that feeling of being in control of the situation.</p>\n<p>At the same time, why would I want to reject something that&#8217;s being offered for free, especially if it delivers on the big promise in the headline (&#8220;Want to learn how to get 5,000 subscribers for free?&#8221;). Plus, it sounds a little silly and over-the-top.</p>\n<p>Naturally, I&#8217;m going to go with the free ebook.</p>\n<h3>26. Use Social Proof</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-ways-to-use-social-proof-to-increase-your-conversions/\">Social proof</a> works because we tend to look to others in order to decide the right thing to do.</p>\n<p>Over 100,000 web developers can&#8217;t be wrong, right?</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94989\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Learnable-e1460608695827.png\" alt=\"Learnable\" width=\"619\" height=\"371\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Learnable-e1460608695827.png 619w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Learnable-e1460608695827-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 619px) 100vw, 619px\" /></p>\n<p>Or how about 310,000+ dog lovers? In fact, if you&#8217;re a dog lover you might be asking yourself, &#8220;Why didn&#8217;t I join this community sooner? If so many others have joined, they must know something I don&#8217;t.&#8221;</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-90403\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/numberspopup.png\" alt=\"Numbers Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"449\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/numberspopup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/numberspopup-300x217.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>These are some pretty impressive examples, but you don&#8217;t necessarily need huge numbers in order to leverage social proof in your marketing. In fact, you don&#8217;t need your own numbers at all. You could simply use someone else&#8217;s numbers or results as an example. Simply point out what others have done, and how your prospect can follow their lead.</p>\n<h3>27. Use Your Credentials</h3>\n<p>Authority is a powerful tool that you can use to increase conversions on your exit popups.</p>\n<p>If you have any special certifications or qualifications that can give visitors greater confidence in your authority and expertise? Show that off on your exit popup!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.timothysykes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Timothy Sykes</a> displays his &#8220;Top Trader&#8221; badge right on his exit popup:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94987\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd;\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Timothy-Sykes-e1460608570937.jpg\" alt=\"Timothy Sykes\" width=\"620\" height=\"374\" /></p>\n<p>Have you <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/6-guest-blogging-mistakes-that-are-costing-you-thousands-of-subscribers/\">written any guest posts</a> for popular blogs? Have you been featured in any magazines? Display all of those logos at the bottom of your popup as <a href=\"http://preneurmarketing.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">PreneurCast</a> does:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94994\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/PreneurCast-e1460608968558.png\" alt=\"PreneurCast\" width=\"620\" height=\"447\" /></p>\n<p>Remember, people have a natural tendency to follow authority figures. Position yourself as the expert, and it will be so much easier to get visitors to take the action you&#8217;re asking of them.</p>\n<h3>28. Use Numbers</h3>\n<p>Numbers can be used in a variety of ways to increase conversions on your exit popups.</p>\n<p>For starters, numbers are great <a href=\"http://www.stipso.com/blog/2015/4/9/7-number-psychology-tips-content-marketing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">attention-grabbers</a>. There&#8217;s just something about seeing a numberespecially a very specific, odd number, like 1,837that causes us to stop and take notice.</p>\n<p>We also know that people have a tendency to <a href=\"http://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/02/professional-help-5-ways-youre-influenced-by-numbers-psychology/251906/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">infer larger sizes</a>, or more of something, from larger numbers. So 660 minutes sounds larger than 11 hours, even though they&#8217;re the exact same amount of time. Use this to your advantage in your popup copy by using smaller units when you want to give the impression of bigger amounts.</p>\n<p>Of course, if you have big amounts to show off, like <a href=\"https://syedbalkhi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Syed Balkhi</a>, then by all means, do it!</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94969\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/socialproofpopup.png\" alt=\"social proof popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"408\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/socialproofpopup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/socialproofpopup-300x197.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>29. Use Arrows</h3>\n<p>Just like great copy, great <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/popup-design-inspiration/\">popup design</a> can increase conversions on your exit popups by drawing the eye where it needs to go.</p>\n<p>Our eyes have the ability to take in so much visual information that it&#8217;s more than our brains can consciously process. So, we&#8217;re hardwired to focus on only the most compelling informationthe information we believe to be the most importantand skim over the rest.</p>\n<p>This is called <a href=\"http://vanseodesign.com/web-design/direct-the-eye/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">selective attention</a>. The result of selective attention is that people naturally look for visual information to tell them what&#8217;s important and what&#8217;s not. Because of this, we can actually direct where the eye will look by guiding their eye using visual cues, like arrows.</p>\n<p>Arrows actually help the viewer comprehend information better than written directions alone. They literally point the way, direct the viewer&#8217;s focus, and help the viewer filter out unimportant information. Use arrows on your exit popups to direct attention towards your call to action.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example from <a href=\"http://kindlepreneur.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Kindlepreneur</a>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95302\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Kindlepreneur-Exit-Popup-e1461297511932.png\" alt=\"Kindlepreneur Exit Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"461\" /></p>\n<h3>30. Use Animation</h3>\n<p>Another way to guide the eye towards your call to action is with movement.</p>\n<p>An animation, like the one below, is nearly impossible for the eye not to follow. In fact, this particular animation points at the call to action button, combining a directional visual cue with movement. The result is an extremely powerful exit popup.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-92904\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd;\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/YbBLDkjW31.gif\" alt=\"YbBLDkjW31\" width=\"621\" height=\"388\" /></p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\"><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/monstereffects/\">Learn how to add animation to your exit popups with a single click.</a></div>\n<p>Hard to look away, isn&#8217;t it?</p>\n<h3>31. Ask Visitors to Follow You on Social</h3>\n<p>Asking for an email address can be tough; due to information overload, people can be fiercely protective of their email addresses these days.</p>\n<p>To ask them to follow you on social media, however, is a bit easier. Especially if your social media channels have a significant following (social proof), it should be relatively simple to get an abandoning visitor to click the &#8220;Like&#8221; or &#8220;Follow&#8221; button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95004\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FourSignmaFoods-e1460609952891.jpg\" alt=\"FourSignmaFoods\" width=\"620\" height=\"528\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FourSignmaFoods-e1460609952891.jpg 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FourSignmaFoods-e1460609952891-300x255.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>32. Assume the Close</h3>\n<p>A particularly gutsy move is to stop asking whether a visitor wants to take action, and just assume that they do.</p>\n<p>On his webinar registration page, <a href=\"http://neilpatel.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Neil Patel&#8217;s</a> exit popup is a simple registration form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-92978\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/assumetheclose_neilpatel.png\" alt=\"assumetheclose_neilpatel\" width=\"620\" height=\"328\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/assumetheclose_neilpatel.png 1240w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/assumetheclose_neilpatel-300x159.png 300w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/assumetheclose_neilpatel-768x406.png 768w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/assumetheclose_neilpatel-1024x542.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Notice he doesn&#8217;t try to sell you on the webinar at all. There&#8217;s no headline or any details about what the webinar is about. He simply assumes that you want to register.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.crazyegg.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">CrazyEgg</a> assumes that you want to buy one of their plans. Rather than trying to sell you on their plans, they simply ask, which one will you choose?</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94968\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Crazy-Egg-Pricing-Plans-e1460606543679.png\" alt=\"Crazy Egg Pricing Plans\" width=\"620\" height=\"407\" /></p>\n<h3>33. Include Testimonials</h3>\n<p>We all know how important testimonials are on sales pages, but what about exit popups? The fact is, your exit popup is a mini sales page. You may be giving something away for free, but you&#8217;re still asking for something in return, whether that&#8217;s an email address or a small action, like following you on Twitter.</p>\n<p>Convince visitors to take action by using recommendations from your customers and subscribers. If you can include a photo of their faces, all the better.</p>\n<p>Kevin Duncan of <a href=\"http://beabetterblogger.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Be a Better Blogger</a> uses a subscriber testimonial on his exit popup to drive home the value of becoming a regular reader and subscribing for updates.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-94977\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/optin-be-a-better-blogger.png\" alt=\"Be a Better Blogger Optin\" width=\"620\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/optin-be-a-better-blogger.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/optin-be-a-better-blogger-300x193.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>34. Use Compelling Button Copy</h3>\n<p>Is your call to action button copy generic, like&#8220;Subscribe,&#8221; &#8220;Download,&#8221; or &#8220;Sign Up?&#8221;<img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f634.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>Sorry, what? Dozed off a bit.</p>\n<p>If you want your button to be clickable and compelling, kiss the generic copy buh-bye.</p>\n<p>Instead, <strong>use copy that focuses on the benefits</strong>visitors will get from your offer.</p>\n<p>For instance, Shoe Money offers free case studies as their <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/3-amazingly-effective-lead-magnets-you-can-create-in-minutes/\">lead magnet</a>. Instead of a generic, &#8220;Download Now&#8221; button, their button copy reads, &#8220;I Want Millions of Dollars Now.&#8221; How&#8217;s that for compelling?</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94998\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ShoeMoney.jpg\" alt=\"ShoeMoney\" width=\"620\" height=\"477\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ShoeMoney.jpg 580w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ShoeMoney-300x231.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also make your button copy more enticing simply by being more specific about what they&#8217;re getting, or the action they&#8217;re taking.</p>\n<p>If you are giving away a coupon, use a specific dollar amount right on the button: &#8220;Get My $10 Off.&#8221;</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95340\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Get-My-10-Off-e1461354376798.gif\" alt=\"Get My 10 Off Button Copy\" width=\"620\" height=\"465\" /></p>\n<p>To give you some inspiration, here are even more great examples of call to action button copy:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&#8220;Start writing&#8221;  <a href=\"https://medium.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Medium</a></li>\n<li>&#8220;Give Basecamp a try  it&#8217;s free for 60 days&#8221;  <a href=\"https://basecamp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Basecamp</a></li>\n<li>&#8220;Find your gym &amp; get membership&#8221;  <a href=\"http://unbounce.com/conversion-rate-optimization/how-to-write-a-call-to-action-that-converts-with-case-sudies/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Anonymous case study</a></li>\n<li>&#8220;Show Me My Heatmap&#8221;  <a href=\"http://www.crazyegg.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">CrazyEgg</a></li>\n<li>&#8220;Build a Manpack&#8221;  <a href=\"https://www.manpacks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Manpacks</a></li>\n<li>&#8220;Send a GiftRocket&#8221;  <a href=\"https://www.giftrocket.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GiftRocket</a></li>\n<li>&#8220;Talk to us&#8221;  <a href=\"https://contently.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Contently</a></li>\n<li>&#8220;Let&#8217;s Do It!&#8221;  <a href=\"https://lessaccounting.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Less Accounting</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>35. Give Visitors a Chance to Win</h3>\n<p>Sometimes visitors need a little extra incentive to take action. Free digital downloads are increasingly common, but physical items tend to have a higher perceived value. So, why not give away something physical?</p>\n<p>You don&#8217;t need to give everyone a physical gift. Just <strong>give them a chance to win</strong> the gift when they sign up for your newsletter.</p>\n<p>For example, <a href=\"https://www.invisionapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Invision</a> gives you an entry into their free t-shirt drawing when you sign up with your email address.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94999\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Invision.jpg\" alt=\"Invision\" width=\"619\" height=\"408\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Invision.jpg 580w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Invision-300x198.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 619px) 100vw, 619px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.yorkdale.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Yorkdale</a> offers an entry into their monthly drawing for a $150 Yorkdale gift card.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-95001\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Yorkdale.jpg\" alt=\"Yorkdale\" width=\"620\" height=\"432\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Yorkdale.jpg 580w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Yorkdale-300x209.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You could also offer additional entries for other actions, like sharing on social media or referring a friend via email. Giveaways are a powerful means of driving traffic to your website, so put them to good use in your exit popup.</p>\n<h3>36. Use a Striking Image</h3>\n<p>Sometimes all you need to grab your visitor&#8217;s attention is a striking image.</p>\n<p>For example, <a href=\"http://www.made.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Made</a> uses this unusual image of a model with chairs stacked on top of each other to grab your attention:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95006\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Made.png\" alt=\"Made\" width=\"620\" height=\"458\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Made.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Made-300x222.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.otokpa.com/2012/12/fedex-advertising-campaign-by-ddb-brazil/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">FedEx</a> uses a map of the globe to illustrate their point in a fun, unexpected way:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95345\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FEDEX_AMERICA.jpg\" alt=\"Fedex America\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FEDEX_AMERICA.jpg 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FEDEX_AMERICA-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://czcareers-solarwinds.icims.com/jobs/intro?hashed=-435776155&amp;mobile=false&amp;width=974&amp;height=500&amp;bga=true&amp;needsRedirect=false&amp;jan1offset=-480&amp;jun1offset=-420\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SolarWinds</a> uses animals and a dash of humor to spice up their ad campaigns:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95353\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Solarwinds-Ads.png\" alt=\"Solarwinds Ads\" width=\"620\" height=\"224\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Solarwinds-Ads.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Solarwinds-Ads-300x108.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Even something as boring as a Band-Aid can be made interesting with an eye-catching image:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-95355\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Bandaid-Ad-e1461380488486.jpg\" alt=\"Band-Aid Ad\" width=\"495\" height=\"700\" /></p>\n<p>Use a dramatic or unexpected image in your exit popup and you&#8217;ll stop your visitors right in their tracks.</p>\n<h3>37. Use Color to Direct the Eye</h3>\n<p>Remember how we mentioned that our eyes can take in way more information than our brains can actually process? Because of that, people look for visual cues to tell them what&#8217;s important and what they can ignore.</p>\n<p>Color is one of those important visual clues. The specific color you use is less important, but how you utilize contrast in color is essential to directing the eye where you want it to go.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/f-shaped-pattern-reading-web-content/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Studies show</a> that the eye naturally skims a website from top to bottom, making forays into the middle from left to right, forming an &#8220;F&#8221; shape.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95359\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/F-shaped-pattern.png\" alt=\"F shaped pattern\" width=\"620\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/F-shaped-pattern.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/F-shaped-pattern-300x152.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you understand this, you can place important elements along that natural F-shaped path, and use color to place greater visual weight on some of those elements.</p>\n<p>Take a look at this exit popup from <a href=\"http://www.marieforleo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Marie Forleo</a>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95008\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/MarieForleo-e1460610508843.png\" alt=\"MarieForleo\" width=\"620\" height=\"375\" /></p>\n<p>Do you see how the color pink was used to place emphasis on certain words? &#8220;We can help&#8221; and &#8220;award-winning&#8221; both pop right out at you, just before your eyes land squarely on the optin box at the bottom.</p>\n<p>Because the &#8220;Subscribe Now&#8221; button is yellow (in contrast to the pink background), and it&#8217;s the only element of that color, it stands out even more than any other element on the popup.</p>\n<h3>38. Incite Curiosity</h3>\n<p>The information gap theory of curiosity is that we get curious when we think there&#8217;s a gap between what we know and what we don&#8217;t know. It&#8217;s like a <a href=\"http://www.wired.com/2010/08/the-itch-of-curiosity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">mental itch</a>that we just have to scratch.</p>\n<p>If you want a surefire way of making your visitors stick around longer, use an information gap to incite curiosity. Once visitors get the curiosity itch, they&#8217;ll have to stick around to satisfy it.</p>\n<p>In this popup, the headline promises to reveal the strategy that Gary Vaynerchuk used to get 832,241 YouTube views:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-95010\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Gary-Vaynerchuk.png\" alt=\"Gary Vaynerchuk\" width=\"621\" height=\"413\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Gary-Vaynerchuk.png 520w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Gary-Vaynerchuk-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px\" /></p>\n<p>Because there is a perceived information gap, visitors will be driven to enter their email out of curiosity.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://socialtriggers.com/power-of-curiosity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Derek Halpern</a> offers five templates for crafting headlines that incite curiosity. These are perfect headlines for your exit popups:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Howd you like to learn about [new remarkable thing] that [desirable outcome]?</li>\n<li>Ever wonder how you can earn [desirable outcome] with [new remarkable thing]?</li>\n<li>Theres a way for you to [desirable outcome] with this [new remarkable thing].</li>\n<li>If you heard about a [new remarkable thing] that could [desirable outcome], would you be interested in learning more about it?</li>\n<li>The key to a [desirable outcome] is to make sure you use [new remarkable thing].</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>39. Get Inside Your Visitor&#8217;s Head</h3>\n<p>By far the best way to get big results from your exit popups is by putting yourself in your visitor&#8217;s shoes, and offering them exactly what they need and want at that moment.</p>\n<p>Ask yourself what are all the possible reasons for a visitor to leave this particular page on my website? Out of those, which are the most likely reasons?</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.countryliving.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">CountryLiving</a> knows that their visitors would love to have one of their mouth-watering meal ideas for dinner tonight. However, the main thing holding them back is time. Most people feel they simply don&#8217;t have the time to cook an elaborate meal. So, CountryLiving swoop in and save the day with &#8220;26 Easy Dinners that Can be Made in 30 Minutes or Less!&#8221;</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-95028\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Country-Living-Exit-Popup.png\" alt=\"Country Living Exit Popup\" width=\"620\" height=\"456\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Country-Living-Exit-Popup.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Country-Living-Exit-Popup-300x221.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t want the easy dinners, well, you&#8217;ll just be ordering takeout then.</p>\n<p>This is exit popups at their best. Get inside your visitor&#8217;s head, solve their reason for leaving, and become their hero.</p>\n<h3>40. Hide Popups from Existing Subscribers</h3>\n<p>If someone has already taken the action you wanted them to take, like subscribing to your email list, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/page-level-targeting/\">don&#8217;t show that exit popup to them again</a>!Do, however, show a different popup, and a different offer, to those visitors.</p>\n<p>There&#8217;s so much you can do with OptinMonster&#8217;s display rules engine, from <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ways-to-use-optinmonster-follow-ups-to-boost-engagement-and-sales/\">follow up campaigns</a>, to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/onsite-retargeting/\">onsite retargeting</a>, and more.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/lHddoRo7gKM?rel=0\" width=\"620\" height=\"348.75\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Maybe there is another action you&#8217;d like them to take to move them further along your sales funnel. Or maybe you want to take advantage of the fact that these visitors are warmer than the others, and ask for something bigger this time around. You could also offer a different lead magnet than you did before and build on that relationship by offering even more value.</p>\n<p>We hope this article has given you tons of exit popup hacks you can use to boost your conversions. Take one of these and run with it, and don&#8217;t forget to see the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/email-popup-best-practices/\">email popup best practices to skyrocket your conversions</a>, and then <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/easy-ab-split-testing/\">run a split test</a> so you can measure your results.</p>\n<p>Which was your favorite exit popup hack? Let us know in the comments!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/40-exit-popup-hacks-that-will-grow-your-subscribers-and-revenue/\">40 Exit Popup Hacks That Will Grow Your Subscribers and Revenue</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"https://optinmonster.com/40-exit-popup-hacks-that-will-grow-your-subscribers-and-revenue/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"26\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"31 Best Email Marketing Automation Tools to Transform Your Business\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://optinmonster.com/31-best-email-marketing-automation-tools/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://optinmonster.com/31-best-email-marketing-automation-tools/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 11 Jul 2019 12:55:40 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:8:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Email Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"automation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"drip\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"email automation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"email marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"email marketing automation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"testing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"tools\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://optinmonster.com/?p=97112\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:619:\"<p>How much time do you spend on your email campaigns every day, performing the same tasks over and over for different subscribers? We&#8217;re here to tell you that there&#8217;s another way to handle those repetitive tasks: email marketing automation. And all you need is the right tools. As luck would have it, we&#8217;re sharing with [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/31-best-email-marketing-automation-tools/\">31 Best Email Marketing Automation Tools to Transform Your Business</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Jacinda Santora\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39207:\"<p>How much time do you spend on your email campaigns every day, performing the same tasks over and over for different subscribers? We&#8217;re here to tell you that there&#8217;s another way to handle those repetitive tasks: email marketing automation. And all you need is the right tools.</p>\n<p>As luck would have it, we&#8217;re sharing with you the 31 best email marketing automation tools we&#8217;ve found for getting the job done.</p>\n<h3>What Is Email Automation?</h3>\n<p>An <strong>automated email campaign</strong> is a series of emails that are sent automatically, triggered by the actions of your subscribers. This is in contrast to &#8220;email blasts&#8221; or one-off email broadcasts that are sent manually to your subscribers.</p>\n<p>At a time when digital marketing is expanding to include dozens of different mediums, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/beginners-guide-to-email-marketing/\">email marketing</a> still remains one of the highest returning assets (4400%!) a business has at its disposal.</p>\n<p>The benefit of email marketing automation is that it lets you unlock this amazing ROI while you sleep! After you set up the email automation, there&#8217;s no action needed. It just works for you, automatically.</p>\n<p>Consider some of the following statistics on email marketing automation:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129643\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/email-automation-statistics.png\" alt=\"email marketing automation statistics\" width=\"620\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/email-automation-statistics.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/email-automation-statistics-300x242.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Email marketing technology is used by more than 80% of companies. But&#8230;</li>\n<li>Only 51% of companies are using email automation to save time and money.</li>\n<li>Automated emailsget click rates 119% higher than broadcast emails.</li>\n<li>Sending an automated <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/university/courses/how-to-create-a-welcome-email-series-that-sells/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">welcome email series</a> instead of a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-write-the-perfect-welcome-email-for-new-subscribers/\">single welcome email</a> can increase revenue by 13%.</li>\n<li>Automated birthday email offers can boost conversion rates 60% over non-timed emails with the same offer.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These are just a handful of stats that prove the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/is-email-marketing-dead-heres-what-the-statistics-show/\">value of email marketing</a>, and automation in particular. There are hundreds of other data points. However, the bottom line is this: if youre going to do well at email marketing this year, you need to use the <a title=\"45 Insanely Useful Content Marketing Tools To Skyrocket Engagement\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/useful-content-marketing-tools/\">tools</a> that will allow you to automate your campaigns.</p>\n<p>Here are the top email marketing automation tools that you should consider.</p>\n<p><strong>Table of Contents</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#driptools\">Drip Email Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#newsletter\">Email Newsletter Apps</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#integrated\">Integrated Email Marketing Automation Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#monitoring\">Email Tracking and Monitoring Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#leadgen\">Email List Building Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#testing\">Email Testing Tools</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"driptools\">Drip Email Tools</h3>\n<h3><a title=\"Constant Contact Marketing Automation\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/constant-contact-marketing-automation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">1. Constant Contact</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Constant Contact Marketing Automation\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/constant-contact-marketing-automation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129209\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/constant-contact-lead-gen.png\" alt=\"constant contact email marketing service\" width=\"620\" height=\"328\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/constant-contact-lead-gen.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/constant-contact-lead-gen-300x159.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a class=\"thirstylink\" title=\"Constant Contact\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/constant-contact-marketing-automation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a> is one of the email providers that we always recommend because its beginner-friendly and offers quick and easy setup.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll also get lots of support to use this email marketing automation tool since Constant Contact rates highly for world-class support, extensive online training, and webinars to help you achieve success.</p>\n<p>Constant Contact is a great tool for everyone, but if you need an email marketing service that can help with managing <strong>event invitations, registrations, and tickets</strong> (Email Plus plan), you&#8217;ll be particularly happy with this choice.</p>\n<h3><a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/drip-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">2. Drip</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/drip-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129618\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/drip-ecrm-email-automation.png\" alt=\"drip ecrm and email automation tool\" width=\"620\" height=\"312\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/drip-ecrm-email-automation.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/drip-ecrm-email-automation-300x151.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>As the name suggests, <a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/drip-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Drip</a> is an app designed for streamlining the drip email process. Its a surprisingly simple tool that packs quite the punch. The app features email gathering technology, pre-made templates, and drag and drop elements for simple creation.</p>\n<h3><a title=\"SendinBlue\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/sendinblue-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">3.SendinBlue</a></h3>\n<h3><a title=\"SendinBlue\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/sendinblue-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133146\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/sendinblue-site.png\" alt=\"sendinblue\" width=\"620\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/sendinblue-site.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/sendinblue-site-300x194.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"SendinBlue\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/sendinblue-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">SendinBlue</a> is a complete marketing automation software that combines both email marketing as well as SMS messages. They offer a drag &amp; drop builder that you can use to create highly-engaging emails, build automated workflows, and segment users.</p>\n<p>You can also use <a title=\"SendinBlue\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/integrations/sendinblue/\">SendinBlue with OptinMonster</a> to segment your email list and send highly personalized emails to your customers at the right time.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.activecampaign.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">4. ActiveCampaign</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.activecampaign.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129612\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/activecampaign-marketing-automation.png\" alt=\"activecampaign marketing automation\" width=\"620\" height=\"215\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/activecampaign-marketing-automation.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/activecampaign-marketing-automation-300x104.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.activecampaign.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ActiveCampaign</a> allows you to create drip emails that are driven by subscriber interaction, behavior, interests, location, history and more. With this tool, you can automate the entire life cycle of a subscriber or customer.</p>\n<p>You can also use <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/connect-optinmonster-activecampaign/\">ActiveCampaign Tags + OptinMonster</a> to activate drip campaigns based on the subscriber&#8217;s behavior on your website.</p>\n<p>If you need a tool that handles marketing automation, comes with a built-in CRM, and performs multi-channel marketing, ActiveCampaign could be the one for you.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.mailerlite.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">5. MailerLite</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mailerlite.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-127515\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/mailerlite-home.png\" alt=\"mailerlite homepage\" width=\"621\" height=\"427\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/mailerlite-home.png 622w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/mailerlite-home-300x206.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mailerlite.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MailerLite</a>features a drag &amp; drop editor, making it easy to set up beautiful email marketing campaigns in minutes. You can personalize, segment, and automate your campaigns using MailerLite&#8217;s advanced targeting features, and their optimization features will ensure that your campaigns are performing their best.</p>\n<p>Better still, you can use <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-to-connect-optinmonster-with-mailerlite/\">MailerLite + OptinMonster</a> to create high-converting MailerLite signup forms and personalize them based on user behavior.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re just starting out, going it alone, or need a simple, intuitive interface, MailerLite just might be the newsletter service you&#8217;re looking for.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://bombbomb.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">6. BombBomb</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://bombbomb.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129613\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/bombbomb-video-email.png\" alt=\"bombbomb video email\" width=\"620\" height=\"342\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/bombbomb-video-email.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/bombbomb-video-email-300x165.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Text-only emails can be boring. Heck, even images are becoming boring in todays media-saturated internet landscape. If you want to effortlessly spice up your emails, then you should consider using <a href=\"http://bombbomb.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">BombBomb</a> to create video-powered drip emails.</p>\n<h3><a title=\"MailChimp\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/mailchimp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">7. Mailchimp</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"MailChimp\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/mailchimp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129619\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mailchimp-email-marketing.png\" alt=\"mailchimp email marketing service\" width=\"620\" height=\"298\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mailchimp-email-marketing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mailchimp-email-marketing-300x144.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/\">Mailchimp</a> allows you to send drip emails to follow up based on website activity, abandoned carts, activity or inactivity, and much more. You can also use <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/connect-optinmonster-mailchimp/\">Mailchimp Groups + OptinMonster</a> to send drip emails based on what the subscriber opted in for, or even based on checkboxes that the user selects on your optin form.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for tons of integrations and an all-in-one solution for inbound campaigns, here you go.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://gumroad.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">8. Gumroad</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://gumroad.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129620\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/gumroad-audience-building-software.png\" alt=\"gumroad audience building software for creators\" width=\"620\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/gumroad-audience-building-software.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/gumroad-audience-building-software-300x201.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Widely known as a place to sell digital products and services, <a href=\"https://gumroad.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Gumroad</a> now has an email feature that lets you gather and store potential customers alongside existing customers. You can then segment based on numerous features and send updates about your products.</p>\n<h3><a title=\"Mailjet\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/mailjet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">9. Mailjet</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Mailjet\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/mailjet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-132815\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/mailjet-e1559816573731.png\" alt=\"Mailjet\" width=\"620\" height=\"357\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/mailjet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Mailjet</a>is a fast-growing email marketing service that offers everything you need to<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/73-proven-and-simple-ways-to-grow-your-email-list/\">grow your email list</a>. They have an excellent drag-and-drop email builder that lets you customize their templates to work for your brand and you can get started for free with Mailjet and still send up to 6000 emails per month, to unlimited contacts.</p>\n<h3 id=\"newsletter\">Email Newsletter Apps</h3>\n<h3><a title=\"AWeber\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/aweber-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">10. AWeber</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"AWeber\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/aweber-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129623\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/aweber-email-marketing-platform.png\" alt=\"aweber email marketing platform\" width=\"620\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/aweber-email-marketing-platform.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/aweber-email-marketing-platform-300x146.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Did you recently add a bunch of new subscribers to your email list? Well, instead of bombarding them with a bunch of past emails, you can use <a title=\"AWeber\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/aweber-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">AWebers</a> Follow Up feature to get subscribers up to speed in a hurry.</p>\n<p>You can also categorize your AWeber subscribers based on what they opted in to on your website using the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/connect-optinmonster-aweber/\">&#8220;ad tracking&#8221; feature + OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for a solid, trusted email newsletter service that&#8217;s been around AND has killer support, AWeber is where it&#8217;s at.</p>\n<h3><a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">11. GetResponse</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129624\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/getresponse-email-marketing-automation.png\" alt=\"getresponse email marketing automation\" width=\"620\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/getresponse-email-marketing-automation.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/getresponse-email-marketing-automation-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If youre like most people, your email newsletters are sent at predetermined times. Shouldnt they be integrated into your calendar then? <a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GetResponses</a> autoresponder tool uses drag and drop features to make calendar management a breeze.</p>\n<p>You can also send highly targeted autoresponders to subscribers based on how they got on your email list using <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/connect-optinmonster-getresponse/\">GetResponse Campaigns + OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want automation tools and responsive templates to create your landing pages, give GetResponse a look.</p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">Newsletters are a great way to stay in touch with subscribers and keep them engaged with your brand. Learn <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-an-email-newsletter/\">how to create an email newsletter</a> with our guide!</div>\n<h3><a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/convertkit-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">12. ConvertKit</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/convertkit-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129625\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/convertkit-email-marketing.png\" alt=\"convertkit email marketing\" width=\"620\" height=\"285\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/convertkit-email-marketing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/convertkit-email-marketing-300x138.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Want some of the more advanced features of a CRM without the price tag? <a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/convertkit-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ConvertKit</a> allows you to send targeted autoresponders to subscribers based on their interaction with your emails with Automation Rules. They even have blueprints that you can use to quickly create <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/6-steps-to-create-an-effective-email-autoresponder-series/\">autoresponder sequences</a> for almost any situation.</p>\n<p>You can also use <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/connect-optinmonster-convertkit/\">ConvertKit Subscriber Tags + OptinMonster</a> to segment your emails based on on-site behavior.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a professional blogger who&#8217;s looking to run ultra-targeted campaigns, you can&#8217;t go wrong with ConvertKit.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://myemma.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">13. Emma</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://myemma.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129626\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/emma-email-marketing-platform.png\" alt=\"emma email marketing platform\" width=\"620\" height=\"210\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/emma-email-marketing-platform.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/emma-email-marketing-platform-300x102.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Nobody likes a generalized email newsletter. Thats why <a href=\"http://myemma.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Emma</a> is a great tool. This powerful tool works with Shopify, Salesforce, and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/connect-optinmonster-emma/\">OptinMonster</a> to gather CRM and sales data and personalize emails based on the subscriber.</p>\n<h3 id=\"integrated\">Integrated Email Marketing Automation Tools</h3>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.contactually.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">14. Contactually</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.contactually.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129627\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/contactually-real-estate-crm.png\" alt=\"contactually real estate crm\" width=\"620\" height=\"295\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/contactually-real-estate-crm.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/contactually-real-estate-crm-300x143.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.contactually.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Contactually</a> is one of the neatest tools on the list. Its a CRM platform that focuses on vetting contacts. It gathers contacts form your email inbox, website, and social media profiles, and then gathers as much information as it possibly can to guide your messaging.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for an email marketing service and CRM for real estate professionals, you found it!</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.hubspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">15. HubSpot</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hubspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129628\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/hubspot.png\" alt=\"hubspot\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/hubspot.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/hubspot-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hubspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">HubSpot</a> is consistently ranked as one of the top marketing automation tools across a spectrum of tasks. One of its top uses involves streamlining email marketing through the use of automated workflows.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.intercom.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">16. Intercom</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.intercom.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129629\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/intercom-automated-email-conversations.png\" alt=\"intercom automated email conversations\" width=\"620\" height=\"245\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/intercom-automated-email-conversations.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/intercom-automated-email-conversations-300x119.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If youre trying to teach your customers/users about your app, <a href=\"https://www.intercom.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Intercom</a> lets you send automated email conversations directly in the app. This gives them assistance where theyre most likely to see it.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.hatchbuck.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">17. Hatchbuck</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hatchbuck.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129630\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/hatchbuck-crm-marketing-software.png\" alt=\"hatchbuck crm marketing software\" width=\"620\" height=\"291\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/hatchbuck-crm-marketing-software.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/hatchbuck-crm-marketing-software-300x141.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Just like Gmail now uses tags to optimize messages, so does <a href=\"http://www.hatchbuck.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Hatchbuck</a>. You can create tags and assign them to specific contacts based on their interests and the stage of the funnel theyre currently in.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://bo.e-goi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">18. E-goi</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://bo.e-goi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129631\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/e-goi-marketing-automation.png\" alt=\"e-goi marketing automation\" width=\"620\" height=\"495\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/e-goi-marketing-automation.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/e-goi-marketing-automation-300x240.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sometimes you want to move beyond email. With <a href=\"https://bo.e-goi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">E-goi</a>, you can break up any email campaign by sending out updates via fax, SMS, or even voice message.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.act-on.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">19. Act-On</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.act-on.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129632\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/act-on-marketing-automation.png\" alt=\"act-on marketing automation\" width=\"620\" height=\"277\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/act-on-marketing-automation.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/act-on-marketing-automation-300x134.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>For large companies that have a bunch of different inbound, outbound, and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/6-lead-nurturing-mistakes-that-are-costing-you-thouosands-of-conversions/\">lead nurturing</a> programs running simultaneously, <a href=\"https://www.act-on.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Act-On</a> integrates them together to maximize their return.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.leadsquared.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">20. LeadSquared</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.leadsquared.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129633\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/leadsquared-lead-conversion-platform.png\" alt=\"leadsquared lead conversion platform\" width=\"620\" height=\"235\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/leadsquared-lead-conversion-platform.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/leadsquared-lead-conversion-platform-300x114.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>As the name suggests, <a href=\"http://www.leadsquared.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">LeadSquared</a> streamlines the lead scoring process by automating email marketing activities and combining them with sales activities for increased efficacy.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.calliduscloud.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">21. SAP Sales Cloud</a> (Formerly CallidusCloud)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.calliduscloud.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129634\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/calliduscloud-lead-qualifying.png\" alt=\"calliduscloud lead qualifying tool\" width=\"620\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/calliduscloud-lead-qualifying.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/calliduscloud-lead-qualifying-300x109.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Another great lead qualifying tool is <a href=\"https://www.calliduscloud.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SAP Sales Cloud</a> (formerly CallidusCloud). This technology automates the process of identifying promising leads while weeding out ones that are deemed to be unqualified or high-risk/low-reward.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.marketo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">22. Marketo</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.marketo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129635\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/marketo-automated-email-marketing.png\" alt=\"marketo automated email marketing\" width=\"620\" height=\"361\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/marketo-automated-email-marketing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/marketo-automated-email-marketing-300x175.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.marketo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Marketo</a> is one of the best overall automated email marketing platforms currently available. It gives businesses the ability to trigger email campaigns based on 40-plus behaviors, which removes much of the guessing game.</p>\n<h3 id=\"monitoring\">Email Tracking and Monitoring Tools</h3>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.getnotify.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">23. GetNotify</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.getnotify.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-97149\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/getnotify.png\" alt=\"getnotify\" width=\"620\" height=\"244\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/getnotify.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/getnotify-300x118.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.getnotify.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GetNotify</a> is a free tool that notifies you the instant your email gets read by the recipient. You just send your emails like you normally would, but add &#8220;.getnotify.com&#8221; to the recipient&#8217;s email address. Your recipient will not see this, and they will not know that you are tracking their opens.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.campaignmonitor.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">24. Campaign Monitor</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.campaignmonitor.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129636\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/campaign-monitor-automate-email-marketing.png\" alt=\"campaign monitor automate email marketing\" width=\"620\" height=\"249\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/campaign-monitor-automate-email-marketing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/campaign-monitor-automate-email-marketing-300x120.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>What good is an email marketing campaign if you cant automate things like testing, tracking, and optimizing? With <a href=\"https://www.campaignmonitor.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Campaign Monitor</a>, you can. It features interactive analytics that are easy to review and act upon.</p>\n<h3 id=\"leadgen\">Email List Building Tools</h3>\n<h3><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing\">25. OptinMonster</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129637\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/optinmonster-lead-generation-software.png\" alt=\"optinmonster is the best lead generation software ever!\" width=\"620\" height=\"271\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/optinmonster-lead-generation-software.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/optinmonster-lead-generation-software-300x131.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>In order for any email marketing drip campaign or newsletter to be successful, you need subscribers. With <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">OptinMonster</a>, you can build high converting forms for your websites and landing pages in just a matter of minutes. Plus, you can segment leads and customers with <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/page-level-targeting/\">behavior personalization</a> and funnel them right into your automated campaigns.</p>\n<p>Read these <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/category/case-studies/\">case studies</a> to see how much success other businesses are having using OptinMonster.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">26. RafflePress</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133626\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/rafflepress-best-wordpress-giveaway-plugin.png\" alt=\"rafflepress is the best wordpress giveaway plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"436\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/rafflepress-best-wordpress-giveaway-plugin.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/rafflepress-best-wordpress-giveaway-plugin-300x211.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>One of the best ways to increase your email subscriber list is by running contests and giveaways. With <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">RafflePress</a>, you can host these contests on your own blog and social media platforms.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.pagemodo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">27. PageModo</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pagemodo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-97144\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/pagemodo.png\" alt=\"pagemodo\" width=\"620\" height=\"295\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/pagemodo.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/pagemodo-300x143.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pagemodo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">PageModo</a> lets you turn your Facebook business page into a professional landing page that can collect leads and increase your subscriber numbers.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://goviral.growthtools.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">28. GoViral</a> (formerly SmartBribe)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://goviral.growthtools.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129638\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/goviral-automatically-share-content.png\" alt=\"goviral automatically share content\" width=\"620\" height=\"343\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/goviral-automatically-share-content.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/goviral-automatically-share-content-300x166.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://goviral.growthtools.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GoViral</a> (formerly SmartBribe) is a 100% free tool that encourages your new email subscribers to share your opt-in with their friends. It customizes your thank you page to include a &#8220;bonus&#8221; incentive for them to share on social media and email. Once they share, they get access to the free bonus.</p>\n<h3 id=\"testing\">Email Testing Tools</h3>\n<h3><a href=\"https://litmus.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">29. Litmus</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://litmus.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129639\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/litmus-email-optimization.png\" alt=\"litmus email optimization\" width=\"620\" height=\"433\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/litmus-email-optimization.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/litmus-email-optimization-300x210.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://litmus.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Litmus</a> is one of the top tools to render testing emails on any device. You can test up to 40 clients and devices with one single click, which cuts down on the time it takes for you to review each and every email combination.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.reachmail.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">30. Reach Mail</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.reachmail.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129640\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/reachmail-email-marketing-platform.png\" alt=\"reachmail email marketing platform\" width=\"620\" height=\"272\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/reachmail-email-marketing-platform.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/reachmail-email-marketing-platform-300x132.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The <a href=\"http://www.reachmail.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Reach Mail</a> testing feature lets users compare direct performance metrics on up to five individual email campaigns at once. It also accounts for things like subject lines, content, and images to show you which emails will perform best.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.cakemail.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">31. Cake Mail</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cakemail.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-129641\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/cakemail-email-split-testing.png\" alt=\"cakemail email split testing\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/cakemail-email-split-testing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/cakemail-email-split-testing-300x121.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Every email marketer needs an automated A/B split testing tool to improve open rates. With <a href=\"https://www.cakemail.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Cake Mail</a>, you can determine which emails will perform best. Theres also a &#8220;Spam Assassin&#8221; feature to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-reasons-why-your-emails-go-in-the-spam-box-and-how-to-make-sure-they-dont/\">ensure emails dont end up in spam folders</a>.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! We hope this article has helped you to find the best email marketing automation tools for your business. What are some of your favorite email marketing automation tools? Check out our list of the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-wordpress-plugins-to-grow-your-business/\">best WordPress plugins</a> to find even more.</p>\n<p>If youre interested in getting started with just one, it should definitely be OptinMonster. <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f60e.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> It has everything you need to capture targeted leads and segment them right into your automated campaign. <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing/\">Sign up for OptinMonster today!</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/31-best-email-marketing-automation-tools/\">31 Best Email Marketing Automation Tools to Transform Your Business</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://optinmonster.com/31-best-email-marketing-automation-tools/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"25 Best Shopify Apps to Increase Sales Instantly [Most Are FREE]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://optinmonster.com/best-shopify-apps-to-increase-sales-instantly/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://optinmonster.com/best-shopify-apps-to-increase-sales-instantly/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 11 Jul 2019 11:00:55 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:9:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"eCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"best shopify apps\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"conversions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"lead generation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"sales\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"shopify\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"shopify apps\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"social media\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://optinmonster.com/?p=115286\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:566:\"<p>Shopify makes it super easy to get set up to sell online right out of the box. And, did you know that there are also hundreds of Shopify apps available to help you grow your business? But, with hundreds of Shopify apps out there, it can be hard to find the ones that will actually [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-shopify-apps-to-increase-sales-instantly/\">25 Best Shopify Apps to Increase Sales Instantly [Most Are FREE]</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Jacinda Santora\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50265:\"<p>Shopify makes it super easy to get set up to sell online right out of the box. And, did you know that there are also hundreds of Shopify apps available to help you grow your business?</p>\n<p>But, with hundreds of Shopify apps out there, it can be hard to find the ones that will actually help you increase sales.</p>\n<p>We know that your revenue can&#8217;t grow without the right tools, so we&#8217;ve done a ton of research to find the <strong>best Shopify apps to increase sales</strong>.</p>\n<p>These apps will help you promote your store, sell your products, reward your customers, and handle inventory and shipping so you can earn more revenue.</p>\n<p>And, many of them are free! </p>\n<p>So, check it, our list of must-have apps for <a class=\"thirstylink\" title=\"Shopify\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/shopify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Shopify store owners</a>. We&#8217;ve even broken it down into categories to make it easier to find what you need, with our top picks for each. <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f381.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#bestshopify1\">Best Shopify Apps for Marketing and Promotions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#bestshopify4\">Best Shopify Apps for Sales Channels</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#bestshopify2\">Best Shopify Apps for Customer Service</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#bestshopify3\">Best Shopify Apps for Products and Inventory</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#bestshopify5\">Best Shopify Apps for Payment Plans</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"bestshopify1\">Best Shopify Apps for Marketing and Promotions</h3>\n<p>First, let&#8217;s start with the best Shopify apps to promote your store.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing\"><strong>1. OptinMonster</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127821\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-shopify-apps-optinmonster-2.png\" alt=\"best shopify apps optinmonster\" width=\"620\" height=\"462\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-shopify-apps-optinmonster-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-shopify-apps-optinmonster-2-300x224.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve got no problem putting <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing\">OptinMonster</a> first on this list of the best Shopify apps to generate leads and increase sales. </p>\n<p>Of all the marketing apps on this list, OptinMonster&#8217;s ability to instantly lift sales easily makes it one of the top apps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cosmetic Capital <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-cosmetic-capital-increased-leads-by-300-using-a-floating-bar/\">increased leads by 300%</a> using a floating bar optin.</li>\n<li>White River <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-white-river-increased-mobile-conversions-150-percent/\">increased sales 35%</a> using OptinMonster&#8217;s responsive popups.</li>\n<li>The Eczema Company saw an <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-email-marketing-strategy-case-study-eczemacompany/\">instant 2.5X boost</a> in conversions after switching from another popup software.</li>\n<li>Scott Wyden Imagery is using OptinMonster to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-scott-wyden-imagery-reduced-woocommerce-cart-abandonment/\">recover 21% of abandoned shopping carts</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/category/case-studies/\">results speak for themselves</a>, but that&#8217;s not all that makes OptinMonster top our list. Our Shopify app also provides seamless integration of your OptinMonster account with Shopify, so you don&#8217;t need to install any special code. You can even use an OptinMonster popup to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-popup-coupon-that-boosts-sales/\">automatically apply discount codes to Shopify carts</a>!</p>\n<p>OptinMonster is the best option to gather email addresses, <a title=\"Shopify Conversion Optimization Guide\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/shopify-conversion-optimization/\">boost eCommerce conversions</a>, and make more sales. You can also target each optin to specific Shopify products, collections, pages, articles, and tags.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-123688\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify_display_rules-2.png\" alt=\"shopify display rules\" width=\"620\" height=\"287\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify_display_rules-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify_display_rules-2-300x139.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>OptinMonster has all the advanced features you need to boost sales:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Showing targeted promotions (like free shipping banners, sales, and more) to visitors based on <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/referrer-detection/\">referral source</a>, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/geo-location-targeting/\">location</a>, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/onsite-follow-up-campaigns/\">onsite behavior</a>, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/device-based-targeting/\">device</a>, and more</li>\n<li>Using <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/exit-intent/\">Exit-Intent Technology</a> or <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/inactivity-sensor-exit-intent-for-mobile/\">InactivitySensor</a> to reduce cart abandonment by gathering email addresses or showing an offer just before visitors leave your site</li>\n<li>Running retargeting campaigns to improve conversions with <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/onsite-retargeting/\">OnSite Retargeting</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/integrations/\">Integrations</a> with your favorite email marketing, content management, and CRM platforms</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here&#8217;s our guide to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-to-integrate-optinmonster-with-shopify/\">integrating OptinMonster with Shopify</a> to help you get started.</p>\n<p>The OptinMonster Shopify app is $49 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>2. TrustPulse</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-132016\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/trustpulse-home-show-bubble.png\" alt=\"trustpulse homepage showing notification\" width=\"620\" height=\"354\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/trustpulse-home-show-bubble.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/trustpulse-home-show-bubble-300x171.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">TrustPulse</a> works to leverage social proof and builds trust with visitors to your site by showing a small popup notification of real-time activity other users have taken while on your site.</p>\n<p>Shoppers are more likely to trust recommendations from other shoppers over advertisers92% more likely, in fact!when it comes to purchasing decisions. With TrustPulse, you can use real activity from real people to increase your site conversions by <strong>up to 15%</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Real-time event tracking for purchases, demo registrations, email signups, and more</li>\n<li>Smart targeting to boost conversions using advanced targeting rules and timing controls</li>\n<li>&#8220;On fire&#8221; notifications to show how many people are taking action in a given period</li>\n<li>Flexible design options to match your site&#8217;s branding</li>\n<li>Actionable analytics to get the stats you need to boost conversions</li>\n<li>Easy setup on any website with no coding needed</li>\n</ul>\n<p>TrustPulse is <strong>free</strong> for up to 500 sessions (single browser or device visiting your site) per month. Paid plans start at $4/month for up to 1,000 sessions to $350/month for up to a million sessions. Or, ask for a custom plan!</p>\n<p><a title=\"Referral Candy\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/referral-candy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>3. Referral Candy</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Referral Candy\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/referral-candy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127846\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/referral-candy-shopifyapp.png\" alt=\"referral candy\" width=\"620\" height=\"448\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/referral-candy-shopifyapp.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/referral-candy-shopifyapp-300x217.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Did you know that every happy customer <a href=\"https://www.groovehq.com/support/customer-support-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">will tell nine more</a>? So, if you&#8217;re not finding a way to get referrals, you&#8217;re missing out on sales.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Referral Candy\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/referral-candy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Referral Candy</a> is one of the best Shopify apps to give your customers incentives to refer their friends. You can choose the reward of your choice for unlimited referrals.</p>\n<p>The Referral Candy system includes automatic reward delivery and referral reminders, as well as a dashboard where you can track referrals. This app starts at $49 per month.</p>\n<p>Want to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/psychograpic-marketing-generates-leads/\">learn more about your customers&#8217; secret thoughts</a> so you can drive even more sales? Here&#8217;s how you can create a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-wordpress-survey-popup/\">WordPress survey popup</a> with OptinMonster.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/smile-io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>4. Smile.io Rewards</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/smile-io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127852\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-smile.png\" alt=\"smile: rewards &amp; loyalty app for shopify\" width=\"620\" height=\"460\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-smile.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-smile-300x223.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Whether customers stick to one brand or not, <a href=\"https://blog.accessdevelopment.com/2018-customer-loyalty-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">loyalty programs</a> can be a huge draw. Customers enjoy engaging with brands, as well as the personalized service and rewards that come with these programs.</p>\n<p>With <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/smile-io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Smile.io</a> you can offer a loyalty program on your Shopify store to create more loyal customers who boost your bank balance with repeat purchases.</p>\n<p>Smile.io lets you issue reward points based on creating accounts, sharing products on social media, following your brand, and more.</p>\n<p>These features are available for free, but you can upgrade to give additional rewards to your VIP customers and to enjoy full customization of your reward program. Upgrade pricing starts at $50 per month.</p>\n<p>Want to keep the interaction going after your customers open their accounts? Check out our guide to the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/7-types-of-emails-that-keep-customers-coming-back/\">7 types of emails that keep customers coming back</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/plug-in-seo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>5. Plug in SEO</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/plug-in-seo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-127844 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/plug-in-seo-app.png\" alt=\"plug-in seo google shopping optimization\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/plug-in-seo-app.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/plug-in-seo-app-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/plug-in-seo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Plug in SEO</a> is our pick for one of the best free Shopify apps because it helps you find, troubleshoot, and fix <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ultimate-seo-guide/\">search engine optimization (SEO)</a> issues so you can get more web traffic to your online store.</p>\n<p>This free app automatically checks for issues with page titles and descriptions, structure, speed, and more. It includes code snippets you can use to fix any issues yourself.</p>\n<p>If you need additional features, like bulk editing, structured data support, and multilingual SEO, you&#8217;ll need to upgrade to the pro version of the app, which is $20 per month.</p>\n<p>Learn more tips to rank higher in search results in our <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/shopify-seo-guide/\">Shopify SEO</a> guide. Or, breathe life into your outdated SEO with these new <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/updating-outdated-seo/\">SEO best practices</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/social-photos\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>6. Social Photos</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/social-photos\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-127849 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-apps-socialphotos.png\" alt=\"socialphotos shopify app lets you sell products with direct links\" width=\"620\" height=\"372\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-apps-socialphotos.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-apps-socialphotos-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Want to drive more Shopify sales from <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-generate-leads-on-instagram/\">Instagram</a>? <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/social-photos\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Social Photos</a> could be the app you&#8217;ve been looking for. This app helps you feature your customers (making them happy) and get an awesome kind of<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-ways-to-use-social-proof-to-increase-your-conversions/\">social proof</a>called <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/user-generated-content/\">user-generated content</a> at the same time.</p>\n<p>When customers tag photos of themselves using your products on Instagram, Social Photos automatically collates them into a gallery. Every photo can then be used to sell products through direct links, driving more sales.</p>\n<p>You can highlight the best customer photos to encourage new customers to buy, and can also create themed products images galleries. Social Photos also lets you interact with Instagram photos from the page where the photos appear.</p>\n<p>You can find Social Photos in the Shopify app store starting at $10 per month for the basic package, and it goes up to $50 per month for the full range of features.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://getpocket.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>7. Pocket</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://getpocket.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-130111\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/pocket-content-curation.png\" alt=\"pocket content curation\" width=\"620\" height=\"371\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/pocket-content-curation.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/pocket-content-curation-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://getpocket.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Pocket</a> is more of a personal content curation tool. And, you need research for knowledge and inspiration, right?</p>\n<p>This browser bookmarklet lets you save content quickly and tag it so you can easily find it later. You can save to Pocket form your computer and view your saves from any device. Seriously. It&#8217;s available on just about every smartphone and e-reader around. Plus, Pocket is integrated with more than 1500 apps!</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s an excellent way to keep a stash of content on your favorite topics and you can get it for free. If you want an ad-free experience, that&#8217;ll run you $4.99/month (or save 25% and get a year at $44.99).</p>\n<h3 id=\"bestshopify4\">Best Shopify Apps for Sales Channels</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/facebook-store\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>8. Facebook Channel</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/facebook-store\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127848\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-apps-facebook-channel.png\" alt=\"facebook channel shopify apps\" width=\"620\" height=\"391\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-apps-facebook-channel.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-apps-facebook-channel-300x189.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>While <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/email-marketing-vs-social-media-performance-2016-2019-statistics/\">email marketing is more effective than social media</a> at driving sales, social media is still an important referral source for online stores. In fact, both Facebook and Twitter can help you gain product recommendations, and actual sales.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128982\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/facebook-channel-screenshot.png\" alt=\"facebook sales channel desktop view\" width=\"620\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/facebook-channel-screenshot.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/facebook-channel-screenshot-300x162.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s why <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/facebook-store\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook Channel</a> makes our list of the best Shopify apps to increase sales. It lets you use your Facebook presence to drive sales, setting a Facebook store up in just a few clicks. With Facebook Channel, you can highlight products on your Facebook timeline and let shoppers purchase products directly from your posts.</p>\n<p>Facebook Channel is a free app. <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f389.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>Check out our guide to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-get-traffic-from-facebook-for-free/\">getting traffic from Facebook</a>to get even more sales from your Shopify store. You can also <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-like-us-on-facebook-popup-with-optinmonster/\">create a custom &#8220;Like Us On Facebook&#8221; popup</a> to drive traffic from your website to your Facebook business page!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/messenger\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>9. Messenger Channel</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/messenger\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128985\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/messenger-channel-2.png\" alt=\"messenger shopify app\" width=\"620\" height=\"319\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/messenger-channel-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/messenger-channel-2-300x154.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>With the growth of messaging apps and smart speakers, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/conversational-commerce/\">conversational commerce</a> continues to grow at a rapid pace. Take advantage of this trend with the <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/messenger\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Messenger sales channel app</a> for Shopify.</p>\n<p>With this free app connected to Shopify, you can add a &#8220;message us&#8221; button to your online store, making it easy to have real-time conversations with your customers. But it doesn&#8217;t end with real-time communications.</p>\n<p>Shoppers can also browse products and make purchases from your Messenger chat and you can send automated order updates.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128986\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/messenger-channel-screenshot.png\" alt=\"messenger mobile sales example\" width=\"620\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/messenger-channel-screenshot.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/messenger-channel-screenshot-300x168.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll be able to fulfill Messenger orders from Shopify and track Facebook sales in your sales channel overview and Analytics pages.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.shopify.com/buy-button\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>10. Buy Button Channel</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.shopify.com/buy-button\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128988\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/buy-button-channel.png\" alt=\"buy button channel\" width=\"620\" height=\"322\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/buy-button-channel.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/buy-button-channel-300x156.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The free <a href=\"https://www.shopify.com/buy-button\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Buy Button sales channel app</a> is simple but effective. You can use it to create a customized buy button that you can put anywhere to let shoppers purchase with a click. No muss, no fuss.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128989\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/buy-button-screenshot.png\" alt=\"but button sales channel screenshot\" width=\"620\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/buy-button-screenshot.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/buy-button-screenshot-300x168.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You can change the button colors to match your brand, create custom checkout links for any product, and update product details from Shopify without needing to edit any code on your eCommerce store or blog.</p>\n<p>With the Buy Button, you can fulfill orders made with both the buttons and just the custom checkout links. And, you can track sales using your Home sales overview and Analytics pages.</p>\n<h3 id=\"bestshopify2\">Best Shopify Apps for Customer Service</h3>\n<p>Next, let&#8217;s look at the top apps for customer service.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/facebook-messenger-live-chat\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>11. Facebook Live Chat</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/facebook-messenger-live-chat\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127850\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-facebook-live-chat.png\" alt=\"facebook live chat\" width=\"620\" height=\"465\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-facebook-live-chat.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-facebook-live-chat-300x225.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Live chat has become an important customer service and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-ways-to-collect-customer-feedback/\">customer feedback</a> tool. According to recent <a href=\"https://www.kayako.com/live-chat-software/statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">surveys</a>, businesses say offering live chat has had a positive effect on sales, revenue, and customer loyalty. And with more than 2 billion users, Facebook is one of the best social media sites to connect with your customers.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/facebook-messenger-live-chat\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook Live Chat Shopify app</a> lets you support your customers on your Shopify site by using <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/facebook-messenger-marketing/\">Facebook Messenger</a> for customer service. The app also integrates with other social sites and features a user-friendly, responsive design.</p>\n<p>This app is free for up to three websites, with upgrade packages ranging from $9.99 to $49.99 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/one-click-social-login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>12. One Click Social Login</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/one-click-social-login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127841\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-one-click-social-login.png\" alt=\"one click social login makes customer onboarding easy\" width=\"620\" height=\"292\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-one-click-social-login.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-one-click-social-login-300x141.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The easier you make it for customers to create accounts, the sooner you can offer them the right products and make sales.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/one-click-social-login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">One Click Social Login</a> lets your customers create accounts on your Shopify store by logging in with their existing social media credentials. Accounts supported include Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, Pinterest, Amazon, and many more.</p>\n<p>There&#8217;s also an easy admin panel so you can easily configure the simple settings.</p>\n<p>One Click Social Login starts at $4.99 per month, but you can upgrade to see your customers&#8217; social profiles and make additional customizations.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/yotpo-social-reviews\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>13. Yotpo</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/yotpo-social-reviews\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127843\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-shopify-yotpo.png\" alt=\"yotpo shopify app\" width=\"620\" height=\"422\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-shopify-yotpo.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-shopify-yotpo-300x204.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/yotpo-social-reviews\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Yotpo</a> consistently ranks among the best apps to increase sales because it helps you get more product reviews to drive purchases from social proof.</p>\n<p>This app lets you easily send out requests for customer reviews and showcase reviews in widgets and store tabs. You can moderate all reviews received, and can also use Yotpo to get social media traffic to your store.</p>\n<p>Yotpo is free, but if you want additional features such as user-generated photos, rich snippets, and more, pricing starts at $29 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/swell\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>14. Rewards and Referrals by Swell</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/swell\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127847\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/rewards-referrals-app.png\" alt=\"rewards and referrals by swell ARE swell\" width=\"620\" height=\"369\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/rewards-referrals-app.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/rewards-referrals-app-300x179.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>One of the reasons we&#8217;ve included <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/swell\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Swell</a>, even though there are both rewards and referrals apps already on the list, is because it has so many integrations. As well as working with Yotpo, which we mentioned above, it works with Facebook, Hubspot, Mailchimp, and more.</p>\n<p>Swell says its users have doubled business from existing customers, thanks to rewards for writing reviews, referring new customers, creating accounts, making new purchases, and more. You can also reward social media interactions such as likes and follows.</p>\n<p>Swell is free for up to 100 orders each month. After that, plans start at $29 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/swym-relay\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>15. Wishlist Plus</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/swym-relay\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127854\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/wishlist-plus-shopify.png\" alt=\"wishlist plus app\" width=\"620\" height=\"257\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/wishlist-plus-shopify.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/wishlist-plus-shopify-300x124.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.huffingtonpost.com/ian-mills/4-ways-wishlists-can-boost-your-website-sales_b_9417882.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Wishlists</a> are a great way to learn more about what your customers want, so you can connect with them to make more sales. <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/swym-relay\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Wishlist Plus</a> lets you collect information about customer preferences, and they don&#8217;t even have to be logged in. </p>\n<p>This app integrates with your Shopify store and lets you keep track of items and engagement within a dashboard. For customers, Wishlist Plus is a hassle-free way to store their desired purchases and even share those with others.</p>\n<p>Wishlist Plus is free for up to 100 items, then plans range from $9.99 to $29.99 per month.</p>\n<p>Want to get even more from your online store? Check out our guide to how to write a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-write-a-sales-page-that-converts/\">sales page that converts</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"bestshopify3\">Best Shopify Apps for Products and Inventory</h3>\n<p>This category includes apps to help you manage your product catalog, plus the periods before and after shipping.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Spocket\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/spocket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>16. Spocket</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Spocket\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/spocket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-132872\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/spocket-dropship-shopify-app.png\" alt=\"spocket dropship shopify app\" width=\"620\" height=\"293\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/spocket-dropship-shopify-app.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/spocket-dropship-shopify-app-300x142.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Spocket\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/spocket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Spocket</a> is a dropshipping marketplace that&#8217;s easy-to-use, quick, and updated regularly. It offers fast shipping of hundreds of thousands of products from more than 20,000 reliable suppliers.</p>\n<p>With Spocket you get one-click order fulfillment, flat-rate shipping, and real-time order trackingall big-time customer pleasers!</p>\n<p>And, in the rare event that something does go wrong, Spocket has a dedicated support team that is ready to help you get it resolved quickly and painlessly.</p>\n<p>You can get started with 25 products for FREE, but up to 250 products is only $29/month (or $69/month for unlimited products!).</p>\n<p><a title=\"Printful\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/printful/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>17. Printful</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Printful\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/printful/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-127845 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/printful-best-shopify-apps.png\" alt=\"printful makes it super easy to sell online\" width=\"620\" height=\"394\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/printful-best-shopify-apps.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/printful-best-shopify-apps-300x191.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you want a Shopify store without the need to warehouse your own products, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/refer/printful/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Printful</a> can help. This app provides print-on-demand designs for T-shirts, bags, mugs, and almost anything else that can be printed. They&#8217;ve even got designers who&#8217;ll help you create the most appealing products.</p>\n<p>Once they&#8217;re ready, just take orders from your store and Printful will send them out. No need to manage inventory or print shipping labels. It&#8217;s a great way to make sales with no hassle. Cost varies depending on the product to sell.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/oberlo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>18. Oberlo</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/oberlo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-127842 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-apps-oberlo.png\" alt=\"oberlo shopify app makes it easy to sell online\" width=\"620\" height=\"394\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-apps-oberlo.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/best-apps-oberlo-300x191.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/oberlo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Oberlo</a> offers a similar service to Printful by letting you add products to your store and dropshipping them straight to your customers.</p>\n<p>But with this app, you&#8217;re not limited to items that can be printed. You can choose products from AliExpress and the Oberlo Marketplace and add them to your store with a couple of clicks.</p>\n<p>Oberlo offers automatic order fulfillment and inventory management. You can also customize products, connect Oberlo with your existing products, and even allow other people to help run your store.</p>\n<p>Oberlo is free for 500 products and up to 50 orders per month. For additional products, orders and features, you can upgrade at between $29.90 and $79.90 per month.</p>\n<p>To get more from using Oberlo products, check out our tips on how to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-email-marketing-tips/\">skyrocket your eCommerce sales</a> with email marketing.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/returns-center-by-aftership\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>19. AfterShip Returns Center</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/returns-center-by-aftership\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127839\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-aftership.png\" alt=\"aftership returns center app\" width=\"612\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-aftership.png 612w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-aftership-300x245.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sometimes your customers will want to return a product, but it can be a pain to manage the process. <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/returns-center-by-aftership\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">AfterShip</a> makes managing product returns easy.</p>\n<p>It gives you a branded returns center that lets customers submit returns in a couple of clicks. Later, it&#8217;ll automatically inform them of the status of their returns and any refunds.</p>\n<p>This is one of the best Shopify apps around, and it&#8217;s free for 5 returns per month. Paid plans start at $9 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/zine-builder\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>20. Catalog Maker</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/zine-builder\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127853\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/wholesale-catalog.png\" alt=\"wholesale catalog maker\" width=\"620\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/wholesale-catalog.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/wholesale-catalog-300x206.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>A product catalog is a great way to show off your products images and boost sales, but how do you create one? If you&#8217;re not a great designer but have a lot of products, you need a tool that makes the process easy. <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/zine-builder\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Catalog Maker</a> could be that tool.</p>\n<p>It lets you quickly create professional looking catalogs from your Shopify collections, and you can use drag and drop editing to create a catalog with one of the app&#8217;s templates.</p>\n<p>In addition to catalogs, you can create invoices, receipts, product recommendations, and even thank you notes. Pricing starts at $25.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/pre-order\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>21. Pre-Order Manager</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/pre-order\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127851\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-pre-order-manager.png\" alt=\"pre-order manager app lets you take advantage of advance sales\" width=\"620\" height=\"359\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-pre-order-manager.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopify-pre-order-manager-300x174.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>When you generate buzz with your seasonal or <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/holiday-email-marketing-tips-examples/\">holiday email marketing</a>, it&#8217;s useful to let people pre-order items from your store. And pre-orders are a great way to figure out which products are most likely to be successful.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/pre-order\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Pre-Order Manager</a> lets you take advance orders from visitors to your store with a pre-order button for out of stock items. You can edit button text, change the setting by location, and even turn pre-orders on and off storewide. You can also limit the number of available pre-orders for any product.</p>\n<p>Pricing for Pre-Order Manager starts at $24.95 per month after a 14-day free trial.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/back-in-stock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>22. Back in Stock</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/back-in-stock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-127840\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-back-in-stock.png\" alt=\"back in stock app\" width=\"620\" height=\"505\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-back-in-stock.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/apps-back-in-stock-300x244.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sold out of your best products? With <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/back-in-stock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Back in Stock</a>, you don&#8217;t need to lose sales. Our last app in the list of best Shopify apps lets your customers sign up to be notified when a product they want is back in your store. Once it is, they get an automatic email notification.</p>\n<p>This easy to install app also helps you understand which products are most popular so you can manage stock levels. You can also customize any aspect of the app to meet your needs.</p>\n<p>Back in Stock starts at $19 per month, with plans up to $79 per month.</p>\n<h3 id=\"bestshopify5\">Best Shopify Apps for Payment Plans</h3>\n<p>Our last category includes Shopify apps that help you get set up to accept recurring and partial payments. This means that you can let shoppers spread out payments on high-ticket items or set up recurring payments for subscription services.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/partial-ly-payment-plans\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>23. Partial.ly Payment Plans</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/partial-ly-payment-plans\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128991\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/partially-shopify-app.png\" alt=\"partial.ly payment plans\" width=\"620\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/partially-shopify-app.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/partially-shopify-app-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/partial-ly-payment-plans\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Partial.ly</a> gives shoppers the option to complete their purchase using standard checkout or with Partial.ly payment plans. If they opt for Partial.ly, once they enter their payment details, the order automatically gets added to your Shopify admin and all future payments are timed and automated.</p>\n<p>As the store owner, you have full control over the fee, down payment, term, and payment frequency. You can also allow shoppers to set up automated or manual payment plans.</p>\n<p>Partial.ly integrates with Stripe, so you&#8217;re covered to accept all major credit cards plus a lot more, and it&#8217;s free to install. They charge 5% + $0.30 per transaction.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/paywhirl-recurring-payments\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>24. PayWhirl Recurring Payments</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/paywhirl-recurring-payments\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128992\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/recurring-payments-orders-app.png\" alt=\"recurring payments &amp; orders shopify app examples\" width=\"620\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/recurring-payments-orders-app.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/recurring-payments-orders-app-300x168.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>With <a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/paywhirl-recurring-payments\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">PayWhirl Recurring Payments</a> your customers will be able to manage their own account details, update their payment and credit card information, add or remove payment plans, and purchase subscriptions on their own, saving time for you and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/user-onboarding-best-practices-to-easily-boost-customer-success/\">reducing friction for your customers</a>.</p>\n<p>For subscription services, PayWhirl has a &#8220;Build a Box&#8221; feature that offers shoppers customizable subscription packages, which is a super cool feature. Subscription boxes are HUGE right now, and allowing shoppers to customize their subscription box could be used as an upsell. FabFitFun does this successfully with their subscription boxes.</p>\n<p>PayWhirl Recurring Payments has a ton of other features like a failed payments management system, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/upselling-tips-and-examples/\">upsell funnels</a>, trial periods, and more. The Shopify app does have a free-to-install version for Stripe; other plans include all payment gateways and start at $49/month and have a 14-day free trial. Successful transaction rates start at 3% and go down to 0.5% as monthly plan costs increase.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/recurring-invoices\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>25. Recurring Payments</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/recurring-invoices\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-128993\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/recurring-payments-app.png\" alt=\"recurring payments shopify credit card app\" width=\"620\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/recurring-payments-app.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/recurring-payments-app-300x168.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://apps.shopify.com/recurring-invoices\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Recurring Payments</a> allows shoppers to buy subscriptions, purchase using payment plans, or pay invoices without login or registration. For subscription customers without an account who want to cancel, they can do so easily by clicking the unsubscribe link in their subscription confirmation email.</p>\n<p>Instead of automatically billing customers, this app allows eCommerce business owners to automatically generate invoices that customers can then pay using whatever method they choose at the time; there&#8217;s no need for customers to remember to make changes or updates to their payment methods in their account.</p>\n<p>Recurring Payments is $15.95/month with a 14-day free trial.</p>\n<p>Before we wrap up, here are some pro tips for choosing the best Shopify apps for your eCommerce site.</p>\n<h3>What to Look for in a Shopify App</h3>\n<p>Shopify apps are a great way to extend the functionality of your eCommerce store. But, if you&#8217;re just starting out, it can be really tough to know what to look for when you&#8217;re trying to choose the apps that are going to give you the features you want without breaking your site.</p>\n<p>Here are 3 simple things to check when looking for the best Shopify apps:</p>\n<p><strong>1. User Reviews and Ratings</strong></p>\n<p>User reviews and ratings are an excellent source of information on how the app works in the wild. Plus, they&#8217;re generally pretty reliable and you&#8217;ll be able to see howor ifthe creator of the app responds.</p>\n<p>You can find Shopify app reviews and ratings by clicking the review link under the app&#8217;s name and description at the top of an app&#8217;s Shopify page or by scrolling down to the bottom of the page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133620\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/spocket-best-shopify-apps.png\" alt=\"spocket shopify app reviews\" width=\"620\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/spocket-best-shopify-apps.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/spocket-best-shopify-apps-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>2. Customer Support</strong></p>\n<p>Support is another thing to consider when choosing the best Shopify apps for your eCommerce site. You want to make sure that you have the support<strong>you</strong> need so you can keep your store up and running for your customers.</p>\n<p>You can find support information for Shopify apps on the sidebar of their app page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133621\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/optinmonster-best-shopify-apps.png\" alt=\"optinmonster shopify app page\" width=\"620\" height=\"165\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/optinmonster-best-shopify-apps.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/optinmonster-best-shopify-apps-300x80.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>3. App Screenshots</strong></p>\n<p>Shopify app screenshots let you see what the interface looks like and will let you know if it&#8217;s something you&#8217;ll enjoy working in. They show up in the<strong>Media Gallery</strong>:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133622\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/optinmonster-best-shopify-apps-2.png\" alt=\"optinmonster shopify app page media gallery\" width=\"620\" height=\"326\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/optinmonster-best-shopify-apps-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/optinmonster-best-shopify-apps-2-300x158.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! Now that you know the best Shopify apps to increase sales, why not get even more sales from your store with a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-run-a-successful-email-marketing-campaign/\">successful email marketing campaign</a>? You can also improve store promotion with these <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/promotional-email-examples-and-how-to-write-your-own/\">promotional email examples</a>. And, check out our <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/shopify-abandoned-cart-recovery/\">tips on Shopify abandoned cart recovery</a> to boost your revenue.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/optinmonster\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a>,<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/optinmonster\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/optinmonster\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">YouTube</a> for more helpful guides, tutorials, and resource lists.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-shopify-apps-to-increase-sales-instantly/\">25 Best Shopify Apps to Increase Sales Instantly [Most Are FREE]</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://optinmonster.com/best-shopify-apps-to-increase-sales-instantly/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"7 Thank You Page Hacks That Will Get You Loyal Fans\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://optinmonster.com/thank-you-page-hacks/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://optinmonster.com/thank-you-page-hacks/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 10 Jul 2019 16:03:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"eCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"boost retention\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"brand ambassadors\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"customer retention\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"thank you page\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"thank you page hacks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://optinmonster.com/?p=133581\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:559:\"<p>Did you know that its 5-10 times more expensive to get a new customer for your eCommerce store than to keep an old one? In fact, a buyers 2nd purchase is considered more important than the first one because repeat customers buy up to 67% more products than new onesalready enough reason to convince new [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/thank-you-page-hacks/\">7 Thank You Page Hacks That Will Get You Loyal Fans</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Lily Ugbaja\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25910:\"<p>Did you know that its 5-10 times more expensive to get a new customer for your eCommerce store than to keep an old one?</p>\n<p>In fact, a buyers 2nd purchase is considered more important than the first one because <strong>repeat customers buy up to 67% more products</strong> than new onesalready enough reason to convince new customers to see your thank you page a second time, right?<img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f609.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>But wait, theres more!</p>\n<p><strong>Returning customers become brand ambassadors who promote you with the most powerful form of marketing, word-of-mouth, for free!</strong></p>\n<p>Thats why you should<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-optimization-guide/\">optimise your eCommerce website</a> thank you page, the last point of onsite interaction with a brand new customer, for repeat interaction and sales.</p>\n<p>In this article, well share 7 fresh ideas to hack your thank you page and start getting loyal brand ambassadors right away.</p>\n<h3>Hack #1: Make Them Fall In Love With You</h3>\n<p>Your new customer may have bought from you to satisfy a need but to keep them loyal, <strong>youll need to satisfy a want</strong>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketingland.com/makes-people-love-brands-love-208923\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Studies</a> show that people want to use a great product especially when there are equally great values behind it.</p>\n<p>If you show your new customer that your core values align theyll be more likely to buy from you time and again, and more likely to move up the relationship ladder into becoming die-hard evangelists too.</p>\n<p>Is your brand fun, high-class, charitable? Whatever it is, using it to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-ways-to-increase-conversion-rates-on-your-thank-you-pages/\">add value to your thank you page</a> is a great way to connect for building loyalty.</p>\n<p><strong>How To Implement This Thank You Page Hack:</strong></p>\n<h3>1. Share A Bit About Your Company</h3>\n<p>Take <a href=\"https://dibruno.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Di Bruno Bros</a>, an eCommerce Culinary store that has perfected their branding with the unique selling point we really love cheese.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133582\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/di-bruno-bros.png\" alt=\"di bruno bros branding example\" width=\"620\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/di-bruno-bros.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/di-bruno-bros-300x126.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Introducing customers to their cheese masters with such fun descriptions and personality immediately after a purchase goes a long way towards creating customer connection and loyalty.</p>\n<h3>2. Use Video To Show Your Brand Personality</h3>\n<p>This video by the online store Halloween Costumes is easily one of my favorite <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/anatomy-of-the-perfect-thank-you-page/\">thank you page examples</a>.</p>\n<p>Its hypervisual (always a winner), its creative, unique and screams fun, just like the purchase intent of the customer! All in all, its a great thank you page strategy.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/1RRMlwXGjDY?rel=0\" width=\"620\" height=\"348.75\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p>For more ways to use video in your marketing strategy, check out these great<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/video-marketing-tips/\">video marketing tips</a>.</p>\n<h3>Hack #2: Kill Buyers Remorse</h3>\n<p>One of the fastest ways to <a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/277570046_The_Effect_of_Buyer\'s_Remorse_on_Consumer\'s_Repeat-Purchase_Intention_Experiences_of_Generation_Y_Apparel_Student_Consumers_within_the_Vaal_Triangle\">stop return business in its tracks</a> is to let customers sit around thinking,<em>Should I have bought that?</em> after a purchase.</p>\n<p>Because if they begin to move even slightly towards <em>uh, maybe not,</em>you&#8217;ll end up with a customer that feels manipulated into buying something they don&#8217;t want and now has negative feelings about your brand.</p>\n<p>You need to kill buyer&#8217;s remorse <strong>before it happens</strong>.</p>\n<p>Its easy to use thank you pages to kick buyer&#8217;s remorse to the curb and boost retention by helping your new customer feel good about their purchase and the decision they just made to buy from <strong>you</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>How To Implement This Thank You Page Hack:</strong></p>\n<h3>Share Testimonials And Social Proof</h3>\n<p>If you have big publications or celebrities saying good things about your brand like <a href=\"https://markhor.com/\">Markhor Shoes</a> below, try adding them to your thank you page to get rid of buyers remorse.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133583\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/markhour-social-proof.png\" alt=\"markhour social proof\" width=\"620\" height=\"180\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/markhour-social-proof.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/markhour-social-proof-300x87.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Testimonials, especially videos from peers also go a long way.</p>\n<p>You can also add social proof using real-time activity from your site using a tool like <a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/\">TrustPulse</a> (you can get started for FREE). TrustPulse shows off the actions taken by actual users and customers on your site using a neat little, customizable popup bubble:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-132986\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/trustpulse-social-proof-notifications-min.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"340\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/trustpulse-social-proof-notifications-min.jpg 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/trustpulse-social-proof-notifications-min-300x165.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>Hack #3: Send Them Scurrying Back Into The Funnel</h3>\n<p>Theres never a better time to sell to a customer than when theyve just bought from you.</p>\n<p>At that point, theyve just progressed from cold or warm to a hot lead and they are in buying mode so promote additional offers and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/increase-your-average-order-value/\">increase your average order value</a> before the pocket closes!</p>\n<p>But isnt that <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/spammy-marketing-practices-that-kill-trust-and-conversions/\">sleazy marketing</a>?</p>\n<p>Actually, it isnt. When done to help your customers make the best choice (not just throwing everything youve got at them) theyll be grateful for your help.</p>\n<p><strong>How To Implement This Thank You Page Hack:</strong></p>\n<h3>1. Share Discounts Or Coupons</h3>\n<p>Our customer <strong>Win In Health</strong> used this strategy to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/case-study-how-win-in-health-used-optinmonster-to-increase-revenue-by-300/\"><strong>increase revenue by 300%</strong></a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-113739\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/wininhealth_10percent_lightbox.png\" alt=\"WininHealth Optin Designed to Increase Conversions\" width=\"620\" height=\"473\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/wininhealth_10percent_lightbox.png 800w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/wininhealth_10percent_lightbox-300x229.png 300w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/wininhealth_10percent_lightbox-768x586.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You could pair this hack with a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/create-countdown-timer-optin/\">countdown timer</a> for a good dose of <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-ways-to-use-social-proof-to-increase-your-conversions/\">FOMO (fear of missing out)</a>. <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\">OptinMonster</a> makes this super easy to do even without coding skills using our drag and drop builder:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-121107\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/drag-and-drop-countdown-timer.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"406\" /></p>\n<h3>2. Cross-sell (A Complementary Offer)</h3>\n<p>Amazon reports that <a href=\"http://www.the-future-of-commerce.com/2013/10/14/ecommerce-cross-sell-up-sell/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">up to 35% of their revenue</a> is from cross-selling and its no surprise.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133584\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazon-related-products.png\" alt=\"amazon related products\" width=\"620\" height=\"256\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazon-related-products.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazon-related-products-300x124.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>People want to buy what People also bought so they dont miss out. Why not implement this powerful<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-marketing-strategies/\">eCommerce marketing strategy</a> and start recommending complementary products on your thank you page today.</p>\n<h3>3. Upsell (A Better Version Of The Original)</h3>\n<p>This is also known as upgrading or, You may like this even better.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-115038\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ecommerce-upsell-examples-phone-comparison.jpg\" alt=\"ecommerce upsell examples phone comparison\" width=\"620\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ecommerce-upsell-examples-phone-comparison.jpg 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ecommerce-upsell-examples-phone-comparison-300x162.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>While <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-boost-revenue-with-an-in-cart-upsell-popup/\">in cart upsells</a> are more popular for boosting revenue, thank you page upsells are still a huge help for people who want better products, especially when you dont want to risk scaring them off with high prices before the initial purchase.</p>\n<p>If you have a higher priced version of the product they just purchased that they may like, try offering them a swap. Theyll thank you for helping them get the best option available.</p>\n<h3>4. Bundle Products</h3>\n<p>Bundle complementary products together and throw in a discount for the best effect!</p>\n<p>Amazon does this very well and you have to agree that it makes for a very compelling offer.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133585\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/example-bundling-products.png\" alt=\"example of bundling products\" width=\"620\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/example-bundling-products.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/example-bundling-products-300x126.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The best part is that this is easy to do when you use the right software (not-so-subtle-hint: <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing/\">OptinMonster</a>). Take a look at some of the awesome<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ways-to-use-optinmonster-follow-ups-to-boost-engagement-and-sales/\">ways people use OptinMonster for better conversions</a>.</p>\n<h3>Hack #4: Make Them Use It To Love It</h3>\n<p>Getting a lead to buy your great product doesn&#8217;t mark the end of your interaction with them. If they dont actually use the product, theyll never know how good it truly is and you miss out on a big opportunity: winning over a repeat customer and a brand advocate.</p>\n<p>Even worse, what if they&#8217;re not using it because they don&#8217;t quite understand <strong>how</strong> to use it?<img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f631.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>Scary, yes, but thats why a great thank you page hack for boosting retention rates is to showcase instructional visuals right there on the thank you page.</p>\n<p><strong>How To Implement This Thank You Page Hack:</strong></p>\n<h3>Share Instructional Videos</h3>\n<p>This is a hack your new customer wont forget in a hurry. By <a href=\"https://www.cloudways.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/Helpful-Resources.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">sharing a helpful instructional video</a> to get them using the product immediately, you remove potential confusion and show thoughtfulness the new customer wont forget.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133586\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/matcha-instructional-video.png\" alt=\"add an instructional video to your thank you page\" width=\"620\" height=\"372\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/matcha-instructional-video.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/matcha-instructional-video-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Another option would be to share how the product is changing the lives of your customers using video or text reviews.</p>\n<p>If you are having trouble getting customers to leave you the raving reviews your product deserves, take a look at our <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/get-more-product-reviews/\">handy guide to getting customer reviews</a>.</p>\n<h3>Hack #5: Win Over Resistant Ambassadors With Incentives!</h3>\n<p>Every eCommerce business should always be on the lookout for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/influencer-marketing-beginner-guide/\">ways to recruit brand ambassadors and influencers</a>.</p>\n<p>One of the best places to do that is on the thank you page.</p>\n<p>Chances are your new customer is still super excited about their purchase so why not get them to share your products with their friends? You get brand awareness and more sales.</p>\n<p><strong>How To Implement This Thank You Page Hack:</strong></p>\n<h3>1. Incentivize Sharing</h3>\n<p>Simply asking people to share wont always cut it. Instead, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-email-marketing-tips/\">create a referral program</a> and ask customers to share or refer a friend for a chance to win a prize.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133587\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/rockstar-products-referral-program.png\" alt=\"create a referral program\" width=\"620\" height=\"354\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/rockstar-products-referral-program.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/rockstar-products-referral-program-300x171.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Works like a charm!</p>\n<h3>2. Incentivize Another Purchase With A Donation To Charity</h3>\n<p>Donations increase sales.</p>\n<p>They make the brand appear more socially responsible and <a href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/releases/291840.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">consequently higher quality</a>, and they make the buyer feel like they are part of something bigger.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133588\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/use-donations-as-incentives.png\" alt=\"use donations to incentivize sharing\" width=\"620\" height=\"284\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/use-donations-as-incentives.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/use-donations-as-incentives-300x137.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Youll agree its smart to use this opportunity to both make a repeat sale and give back to your favorite charity at the same time.</p>\n<h3>Hack #6: Be The Caring Company</h3>\n<p>Research shows that <a href=\"http://www.reputationxl.com/charts-infographics/68-of-customers-leave-you-if-you-dont-care-for-them/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">68% of customers</a> will leave a company if they dont think it cares about them.</p>\n<p>You should show your visitors that you care about them throughout the <strong>entire lead nurturing process</strong>, and the thank you page is a great way to start customers off letting them know that nothing has changed just because you have their money.</p>\n<p>Theyll leave feeling theyve finally found the right brand and will come back again.</p>\n<p><strong>How To Implement This Thank You Page Hack:</strong></p>\n<h3>1. Share Relevant Articles With Them</h3>\n<p>Using <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/real-time-behavior-automation/\">OptinMonsters behaviour tracking features</a> youll be able to share some articles, reports or whitepaper they may enjoy. That way theyll know its not just about the sale.</p>\n<p>You can even go ahead and ask directly, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/conversational-commerce/\">using conversations to build loyalty</a>. Take a look at this <a href=\"https://conversionxl.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/image16-2-768x367.png\">innovative thank you page</a> UI (user interface) from ChefSteps, for example.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133589\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/chefsteps-thank-you-page.png\" alt=\"share relevant articles with your customers\" width=\"620\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/chefsteps-thank-you-page.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/chefsteps-thank-you-page-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After youve made your choice you are presented with recommendations. Its a great way to hack your thank your page and build loyalty with your customer.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133590\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/chefsteps-thank-you-page-2.png\" alt=\"thank you page recommendations after topics are selected\" width=\"620\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/chefsteps-thank-you-page-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/chefsteps-thank-you-page-2-300x143.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>2. Survey Them</h3>\n<p>Most people actually enjoy surveys and want to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-ways-to-collect-customer-feedback/\">share their opinion</a> because it makes them feel like they have a say in brand decisions, so definitely be sure to hit your visitors and customers up for their opinions!</p>\n<p>The best part, they will come back for a repeat purchase if only to confirm that you implemented their tip.</p>\n<p>The key is to do it right by asking very little of them and doing it progressively. A big form all at once is a no-no.</p>\n<p><strong>Kennedy Blue</strong>, an OptinMonster customer, was able to gain valuable feedback from <strong><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/overcoming-sales-objections-with-popups/\">7% of abandoning shoppers</a></strong> by using this exit-intent popup survey on their checkout page:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-119504\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/kennedyblue_optinmonster_exitsurvey1.jpg\" alt=\"kennedyblue exit survey\" width=\"620\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/kennedyblue_optinmonster_exitsurvey1.jpg 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/kennedyblue_optinmonster_exitsurvey1-300x167.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>3. Implement A Chatbot</h3>\n<p>Think of it as an <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/user-onboarding-best-practices-to-easily-boost-customer-success/\">onboarding process</a>or killer customer support for your new customer and add a chatbot to your thank you page using <a title=\"How to Connect OptinMonster with ManyChat\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/connect-optinmonster-manychat/\">OptinMonsters chatbot feature</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-124894\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/chatbot-gift.png\" alt=\"conversational commerce 2018\" width=\"620\" height=\"395\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/chatbot-gift.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/chatbot-gift-300x191.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>Hack #7: Make Them Sign Up For Remarketing</h3>\n<p>In business, out of sight is out of mind so another great thank you page hack is to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-lead-generation/\">encourage email sign ups</a> and social follows so that you have a way to reach them in future.</p>\n<p><strong>How To Implement This Thank You Page Hack:</strong></p>\n<h3>1. Incentivize Social Media Follows</h3>\n<p>Now is a good time to ask them to follow you on social, but youll have to be creative about it.</p>\n<p>Pottery Barn promises an irresistible reason to follow; for the chance to get products at up to 75% off in an upcoming sale, no one wants to miss that.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133591\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pottery-barn-email-offer.png\" alt=\"pottery barn email offer\" width=\"437\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pottery-barn-email-offer.png 437w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pottery-barn-email-offer-219x300.png 219w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 437px) 100vw, 437px\" /></p>\n<h3>3. Incentivize Signup With Deals</h3>\n<p>People love deals and it makes a perfect thank you page hack for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/mid-funnel-marketing-tactics/\">lead nurturing</a>. Make them sign in for remarketing by hinting an upcoming deal. See how Amazon does it below.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133592\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazon-get-notified-when-deals-go-live.png\" alt=\"amazon sign up for deal notifications\" width=\"620\" height=\"376\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazon-get-notified-when-deals-go-live.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazon-get-notified-when-deals-go-live-300x182.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Use this hack on your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-win-more-sales-with-out-of-stock-pages/\">out of stock</a> pages too for double effect!</p>\n<h3>4. Coupon Codes Free Shipping And Discounts</h3>\n<p>This is one thank you page hack nobody can seem to resist. When someone is already interested enough in your brand to take action, theyll definitely sign up for discounts and coupons.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133593\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/home-fabric-rugs-coupon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"303\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/home-fabric-rugs-coupon.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/home-fabric-rugs-coupon-300x147.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Learn how to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-popup-coupon-that-boosts-sales/\">create a popup coupon on your thank you pages with OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n<p>Or, if you want to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/gamification-in-marketing/\">gamify the popup experience</a>, use our<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/coupon-wheel-optins/\">Spin-to-win feature</a>(requires a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing/\"><strong>Growth plan</strong></a>).</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-132172\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/optinmonster-coupon-wheel.png\" alt=\"optinmonster coupon wheel optin\" width=\"620\" height=\"324\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/optinmonster-coupon-wheel.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/optinmonster-coupon-wheel-300x157.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>5. Push Membership Signups</h3>\n<p>Thrive Market promotes <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/wordpress-membership-site-plugins/\">membership signups</a> over everything else.</p>\n<p>Treat your new customer to a VIP experience and promote your membership offer immediately after signup.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133595\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/thrive-membership-site.png\" alt=\"create an exclusive membership site\" width=\"620\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/thrive-membership-site.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/thrive-membership-site-300x126.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>There you have it! All 7 eCommerce thank you page optimization hacks you can implement today to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ways-to-use-optinmonster-follow-ups-to-boost-engagement-and-sales/\">boost retention and conversions</a>, and win loyal brand ambassadors.</p>\n<p>Which thank you page hacks will you be implementing? Let us know in the comments and dont forget, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\">OptinMonster</a> is the most trustedand bestconversion rate optimization plugin in the world, we&#8217;d love to see you try it out with these tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/thank-you-page-hacks/\">7 Thank You Page Hacks That Will Get You Loyal Fans</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://optinmonster.com/thank-you-page-hacks/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"How to Measure Your Content Marketing ROI + 7 Metrics That Matter\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-measure-content-marketing-roi-metrics/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-measure-content-marketing-roi-metrics/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 09 Jul 2019 21:45:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Content Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"content marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"content marketing ROI\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"lead generation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"social media\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"traffic\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://optinmonster.com/?p=110727\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:591:\"<p>We need to talk about content marketing ROI (return on investment). Do you know what it is? Do you know what yours is? Do you know how to track it? Content marketing ROI is important, but if you wouldn&#8217;t know a successful content marketing program if it walked right up to you and introduced itself, [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-measure-content-marketing-roi-metrics/\">How to Measure Your Content Marketing ROI + 7 Metrics That Matter</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Jacinda Santora\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37146:\"<p>We need to talk about content marketing ROI (return on investment).</p>\n<p>Do you know what it is? Do you know what <strong>yours</strong> is? Do you know how to track it?</p>\n<p>Content marketing ROI is important, but if you wouldn&#8217;t know a successful content marketing program if it walked right up to you and introduced itself, you&#8217;re not alone.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re going to change all that.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;re going to teach you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What is content marketing ROI</li>\n<li>How to measure your content marketing ROI</li>\n<li>What metrics you need to track your content marketing ROI</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Plus, you&#8217;ll also learn other ways content marketing can benefit your businessand if those indirect benefits can be measured (spoiler alert: they can).</p>\n<p class=\"om-callout\"><b>Recommended Resource: </b> Need to jumpstart your content marketing results? Get more traffic and conversions with our <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/content-marketing-guide/?utm_source=om_blog&amp;utm_medium=callout\">Ultimate Guide to Content Marketing in 2018</a>.<p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a <strong>table of contents</strong> in case you want to skip to a specific section of this guide:</p>\n<p><strong>Content Marketing ROI Basics</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#whatisroi\">What Is Content Marketing ROI?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#roiformula\">How to Measure Content Marketing ROI</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The Content Marketing Metrics That Matter</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#cmleads\">Lead Quality</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#cmsales\">Sales</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#cmtraffic\">Web Traffic</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#cmonsite\">Onsite Engagement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#cmsocial\">Social Media ROI</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#cmseo\">SEO Success</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#cmauthority\">Exposure and Authority</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"whatisroi\">What Is Content Marketing ROI?</h3>\n<p><strong>Content marketing ROI</strong> is a percentage that shows how much revenue you gained from content marketing in comparison to what you spent.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133543\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/content-marketing-roi-defined.png\" alt=\"content marketing roi defined\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/content-marketing-roi-defined.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/content-marketing-roi-defined-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>ROI is said to be one of the most important measures of successful content marketing because it&#8217;s directly tied to revenue.</p>\n<p>But money can&#8217;t be your only measure of a successful content marketing strategy, right? If you&#8217;re not getting pageviews, shares, and visitors aren&#8217;t engaging with your content, you&#8217;re not likely to earn any revenue from it.</p>\n<p>To get a clear picture of your content marketing ROI, it&#8217;simportant to think about <strong>which content marketing metrics really matter</strong>. We&#8217;re going to look at 7 important metrics later in this article.</p>\n<p>First, though, let&#8217;s take a look at the <strong>content marketing ROI formula</strong>. This is how you&#8217;re going to figure out exactly how much your content marketing is earning you.</p>\n<h3 id=\"roiformula\">How to Measure Content Marketing ROI</h3>\n<p>There&#8217;s a simple, 4-step content marketing formula to weigh the cost of your content against the revenue you earn from it. Here&#8217;s how you work it out:</p>\n<p><strong>Step 1. Calculate how much you spent to produce the content.</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133546\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-cost-to-produce-your-content.png\" alt=\"calculate cost to produce your content\" width=\"620\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-cost-to-produce-your-content.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-cost-to-produce-your-content-300x188.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Even if you produce your content in-house, there&#8217;s still a cost attached, because you&#8217;re paying the content creator&#8217;s salary or work done by other departments.</p>\n<p>And, don&#8217;t forget to include any external content assets you had to pay for, like <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/places-to-find-images-for-better-conversions/\">images</a>, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/video-marketing-statistics-what-you-must-know/\">video</a>, audio or other outsourced work.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 2: Figure out what it cost you to distribute the content.</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133547\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-cost-to-distribute-your-content.png\" alt=\"calculate the cost to distribute your content\" width=\"620\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-cost-to-distribute-your-content.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-cost-to-distribute-your-content-300x188.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Again, don&#8217;t forget those in-house costs. Include any paid promotions, like <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-boost-the-roi-of-ppc-campaigns-with-targeted-optins/\">PPC advertising</a> and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/23-tools-that-will-take-your-social-media-marketing-to-the-next-level/\">social advertising</a>, as well as promotion through other media channels.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll also need to include the cost of any special tools or software required for either content creation or content distribution.</p>\n<p>Once you add up all of the expenses from Step 1 and Step 2, you&#8217;ll know the true cost of producing your content.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 3: Work out the dollar amount for what you got in return.</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133548\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-sales-directly-from-content.png\" alt=\"calculate sales directly from your content\" width=\"620\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-sales-directly-from-content.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-sales-directly-from-content-300x188.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If your content is working well, it&#8217;ll generate leads that turn into sales.</p>\n<p>Sometimes, there&#8217;s a clear link between content and revenue, like when people read a piece of content and then click on your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-the-perfect-call-to-action/\">call to action</a> to buy something.</p>\n<p>Other times, that process takes longer and the relationship between content and sales isn&#8217;t as direct. We&#8217;ll look at some of those less obvious content marketing metrics later in this guide.</p>\n<p>But if you <strong>add up all the sales that resulted from a piece of content</strong>, you&#8217;ll know how much you earned, which is your return.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 4: Calculate your content marketing ROI.</strong></p>\n<p>To calculate your final content marketing ROI, we really like the simple content marketing ROI formula from <a href=\"http://www.convinceandconvert.com/content-marketing/the-formula-to-calculate-content-marketing-roi/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Convince and Convert</a>: &#8220;Return minus investment, divided by investment, expressed as a percentage&#8221;.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example of how that works:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133549\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-content-marketing-roi.png\" alt=\"calculate your content marketing roi\" width=\"620\" height=\"310\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-content-marketing-roi.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/calculate-content-marketing-roi-300x150.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If you spend $500 on creating a piece of content and get leads worth $2000, then your ROI is 300%.</p>\n<p>(<strong>Return</strong>) $2000 &#8211; (<strong>Investment</strong>) $500 = $1500</p>\n<p>$1500 / $500 = 3</p>\n<p>3 x 100% = 300% (<strong>ROI</strong>)</p>\n<p>So, how do you know if it&#8217;s worth it? Here&#8217;s a pretty good rule to follow:<strong>if you spend less on producing content than you earn in sales, then it&#8217;s worth it.</strong></p>\n<p>Now that you understand how to work out content marketing ROI, we&#8217;re going to look at some of the <strong>key metrics</strong> that help you understand and report on content marketing ROI even better.</p>\n<p>We already covered that content marketing success isn&#8217;t always about money; we&#8217;ll also look at some less tangible metrics below.</p>\n<p>Before we get started, you&#8217;ll need to have Google Analytics set up on your site. If you&#8217;re using WordPress, you&#8217;ll definitely want to check out one of these awesome <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-google-analytics-plugins/\">Google Analytics plugins</a> for WordPress.</p>\n<h3>Content Marketing Metrics That Matter</h3>\n<p>There are 7 key content marketing metrics that matter: lead quality, sales, web traffic, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/onsite-retargeting/\">onsite engagement</a>, social media engagement, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ultimate-seo-guide/\">SEO success</a>, and exposure and authority. We&#8217;ll take a look at how to measure each one in detail below.</p>\n<p>Before we get started, remember that<strong>you don&#8217;t have to track every single metric</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>So, Which Content Marketing Metrics Should You Track?</strong></p>\n<p>Instead of trying to track all of the content marketing metrics all the time, you may find it easierand more rewardingto choose a few metrics to track depending on your goals. For example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If you&#8217;re writinga long pillar article to attract links to your site and boost your search engine rankings, set specific goals for the results you want. Then be sure to track new backlinks to that post and to your site, and monitor your search engine rankings after publication.</li>\n<li>If you&#8217;re planning a social media campaign to build buzz around a new product launch, track the exposure and authority metrics listed below, like media mentions, and keep an eye on your social media engagement.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To determine your content marketing ROI, it always helps to <strong>plan ahead</strong>, <strong>set specific goals</strong>, and <strong>choose just a few meaningful metrics to track</strong>.</p>\n<p>Ready to get started?</p>\n<h3>Does Your Content Have the Potential to Earn Money?</h3>\n<p>The first two metrics we&#8217;ll look at help us answer this question. To measure the earnings potential of your content, you&#8217;ll need to look at leads and sales.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cmleads\">1. Lead Quality</h3>\n<p>As our <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/lead-generation/\">guide to lead generation</a> says, great content attracts an audience, and an audience can generate leads. That&#8217;s why <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/step-by-step-guide-to-generate-leads-with-your-content-marketing/\">content marketing is so crucial for lead generation</a>.</p>\n<p>There are a lot of ways to measure lead quality. For example, if you&#8217;ve just created an epic blog post with a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/9-lead-magnets-to-increase-subscribers/\">lead magnet</a> or <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/30-content-upgrade-ideas-to-grow-your-email-list/\">content upgrade</a>, you can tell it&#8217;s working to attract quality leads if:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>People read your blog post and grab your lead magnet, which shows they could be thinking about doing business with you.</li>\n<li>Your visitors check out related resources that are part of your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/18-ways-increasing-conversions-throughout-your-sales-funnel/\">marketing or sales funnel</a>.</li>\n<li>Visitors contact your sales team to ask pre-sales questions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These actions indicate that your content is generating qualified leads, who are likely to buy eventually.</p>\n<p>One way to track whether your visitors are qualified is to see whether they&#8217;re visiting important pages on your site, like your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing-page-best-practices/\">pricing page</a>. To do so, you&#8217;ll need to <a title=\"How to Create OptinMonster Event Goals in Google Analytics\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/optinmonster-event-goals-google-analytics/\">set up goals in Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve set your analytics goals, go to <strong>Conversions  Goals  Funnel Visualization</strong> to see which pieces of content help turn people into leads.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example from a freelance writer. On this site, 30.37% of the people who looked at the Trial Page ended up on the checkout page, which shows they are interested in testing these services, making them qualified leads.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133553\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-funnel-visualization.png\" alt=\"funnel visualization for goals in google analytics\" width=\"620\" height=\"232\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-funnel-visualization.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-funnel-visualization-300x112.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re getting a lot of traffic but have a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/12-tips-to-reduce-bounce-rate-and-boost-your-conversions/\">high bounce rate</a> and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/reasons-your-ecommerce-site-has-a-low-conversion-rate/\">low conversions</a>, that&#8217;s an indicator that the leads you&#8217;re attracting are low quality, and aren&#8217;t looking for what you have to offer.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cmsales\">2. Sales</h3>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;re going to look at how many of these leads turn into sales, and what the value of those sales is. That&#8217;ll give you one of the key numbers in the content marketing ROI calculation we shared earlier.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;ve got qualified leads and are nurturing them with the right content at the right time, then some of those people should buy something.</p>\n<p>You can get exact numbers on this in Google Analytics by navigating to <strong>Behavior  Site Content  All Pages</strong> if you&#8217;ve <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/enable-ecommerce-tracking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">enabled eCommerce in Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n<p>In this view, the <strong>Page Value</strong> column shows you the average value for a page that a user visited before landing on the goal page or completing an eCommerce transaction. This stat gives you a general idea of which pages on your site contribute more to your site&#8217;s revenue.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133554\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-page-value.png\" alt=\"page value from google analytics is a valuable content marketing roi metric\" width=\"620\" height=\"146\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-page-value.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-page-value-300x71.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Still, this only tracks conversions that happen during one session. Content marketing isn&#8217;t always that linear.</p>\n<p>What if a visitor reads a blog post they found through Google, leaves your site to do some comparison shopping and research, then returns to your site the next day to make a purchase?</p>\n<p>You can also track this through Google Analytics using Assisted Conversions. Assisted Conversions measure the number of conversions that a channel (such as paid ads or organic search) assisted with, at any point along the customer&#8217;s journey.</p>\n<p>To see which channels are assisting in your conversions, you can go to <strong>Conversions  Multi-Channel Funnels  Assisted Conversions</strong>. Just click on a channel and look at the <strong>Lead or Click Direct Conversion Value</strong> column to see how much money it generated, directly and indirectly.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133555\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-assisted-conversions.png\" alt=\"google analytics assisted conversions reporting for content marketing roi\" width=\"620\" height=\"265\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-assisted-conversions.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-assisted-conversions-300x128.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As well as tracking current performance, pay attention to content performance over time, since some pieces of content may become more or less relevant, and drive more or fewer leads and sales.</p>\n<p>You can do this by adjusting the date parameters in whatever tool you&#8217;re using. Here&#8217;s how you change the dates in Google Analytics:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133556\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-calendar-customize-date-range-1.png\" alt=\"customize date range in google analytics\" width=\"620\" height=\"373\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-calendar-customize-date-range-1.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-calendar-customize-date-range-1-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Go to the top right of the screen and click on the date to open up the calendar.</p>\n<p>You can choose a preset time period, like the past week or month from the dropdown menu, or put in your own start and end dates by scrolling through the calendar.</p>\n<p>Click the small <strong>Compare to:</strong>checkbox to compare the selected data to the previous period, to see if your conversions and sales are increasing or decreasing over time.</p>\n<p>Hit <strong>Apply</strong>, and your data will automatically refresh. You&#8217;ll continue to see data for this period as you move through the Analytics app.</p>\n<p>This tells you which pieces of content are more successful long term, and will help you decide if they should be part of your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/18-ways-increasing-conversions-throughout-your-sales-funnel/\">sales funnel</a>. This will be an important part of any content marketing ROI report.</p>\n<p>Since leads and sales translate directly into income, they make it easy to measure content marketing ROI. The next 2 content marketing metrics we&#8217;ll be discussing are all about engagement.</p>\n<h3>Is Your Content Driving Engagement?</h3>\n<p>As a performance metric, engagement is a bit harder to translate into revenue, but it&#8217;s still worth tracking if you want to get a full picture of your content marketing ROI.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cmtraffic\">3. Web Traffic</h3>\n<p>Website traffic is the foundation of content marketing success<strong>without traffic, there is no revenue</strong>.</p>\n<p>It sounds dramatic, right? If there were a content marketing<em>telenovela</em> (<em>ElMarketing de Contenidos de la Pasin</em>, let&#8217;s say)the main character would absolutely fall into a chair, gasping, &#8220;<em>Sin trfico, no hay ingresos.</em>&#8221; as the wind blows her hair.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133561\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/telenovela.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" /></p>\n<p>Dramatic, but true. If nobody is looking at your content, nobody is buying from your content.</p>\n<p>To find out how much traffic a piece of content is generating for your site, you can once again turn to Google Analytics. In the main menu, click on <strong>Behavior  Site Content  Landing Pages</strong>. This report will show you which pages your website visitors are first landing on. By default, it&#8217;s sorted by your highest-traffic pages first.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133563\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-landing-pages.png\" alt=\"landing pages with the most traffic show the most popular content\" width=\"620\" height=\"259\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-landing-pages.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-landing-pages-300x125.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Besides just looking at your raw traffic numbers, you can also look at how your traffic is growing over time by comparing time periods as shown above.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s also a good idea to take a look at where your traffic is coming from; this is known as <strong>referral traffic</strong>. When you know the source of your traffic, you can figure out which part of your marketing strategy is driving traffic with the potential to convertand which parts are wasting your time.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a quick trick you can use to find out where traffic is coming from to your most popular landing pages:</p>\n<p>From the landing pages report, click on the page you want to analyze. Then, click the <strong>Secondary Dimension</strong> button and click on <strong>Acquisition  Source/Medium</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133564\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-source-to-landing-page-report.png\" alt=\"add source to landing page report\" width=\"620\" height=\"382\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-source-to-landing-page-report.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-source-to-landing-page-report-300x185.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you&#8217;ll be able to see where your traffic is originating from for that landing page. In this example, you can see that most people land on this page by searching on Google:</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133565\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/landing-page-acquisition-source.png\" alt=\"landing page acquisition source\" width=\"620\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/landing-page-acquisition-source.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/landing-page-acquisition-source-300x146.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If you see results like this when you&#8217;re spending a lot of time promoting your content on social media, you&#8217;ll know that something isn&#8217;t working with your social media marketing strategy.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cmonsite\">4. Onsite Engagement</h3>\n<p>Content marketing success isn&#8217;t just about getting people to your site; it&#8217;s also about keeping them there. If you have a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/4-ways-to-reduce-your-bounce-rate-with-optinmonster/\">low bounce rate</a>, and people are spending a while on your site, or even coming back, then you know your content is working and you&#8217;re well on the way to generating leads and sales from your content.</p>\n<p>If people land on your epic blog post and leave within a few seconds, you&#8217;ve got a problem. But if your analytics data shows they are reading to the end, and even checking out other content or subscribing to your newsletter, then you know that content is successful.</p>\n<p>For a quick and easy way to see whether or not your website content is attracting quality leads, take a look at your <strong>engagement metrics</strong>. Measuring the way your website visitors interact with your content is a good way to make sure you&#8217;re attracting traffic that&#8217;s interested in what you have to offer.</p>\n<p>To get an overview of your engagement metrics, go to <strong>Audience  Overview</strong> in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133566\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-audience-overview.png\" alt=\"google analytics audience overview\" width=\"620\" height=\"138\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-audience-overview.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-audience-overview-300x67.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Some important stats you&#8217;ll want to look at here are pages per session, average session duration, and your bounce rate. Engaged visitors will spend more time on your site and view more pages if they&#8217;re interested in what you have to offer.</p>\n<p>To find the bounce rate for an individual piece of content, go to <strong>Behavior  Site Content  All Pages</strong>.</p>\n<p>Browse through the list of URLs till you find the content, or type its URL into the search box on the right of the table.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133567\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/bounce-rate-from-google-analytics.png\" alt=\"bounce rate from google analytics\" width=\"620\" height=\"129\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/bounce-rate-from-google-analytics.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/bounce-rate-from-google-analytics-300x62.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Here you can look at the engagement metrics for all visitors who found your site through a specific landing page.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cmsocial\">5. Social Media ROI</h3>\n<p>Offsite engagement is also important for assessing content marketing ROI. If people find your content useful, they&#8217;ll usually link to it or share it with others on social media.</p>\n<p>Social media engagement and referral traffic are important to keep track of because a lot of purchase decisions are influenced by <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-ways-to-use-social-proof-to-increase-your-conversions/\">peer recommendations and other social proof</a>. And guess where your potential customers are hanging out? On social media sites like <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-generate-leads-on-instagram/\">Instagram</a>, Snapchat, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/using-twitter-for-lead-generation/\">Twitter</a>, and Facebook.</p>\n<p>Here are a couple of easy ways to track your content&#8217;s social media engagement:</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking Social Engagement in Google Analytics</strong></p>\n<p>To see how much traffic you&#8217;re getting from individual social media platforms to your website in Google Analytics, you can go to <strong>Acquisition  Social  Network Referrals</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133568\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/social-network-referrals.png\" alt=\"social network referrals\" width=\"620\" height=\"297\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/social-network-referrals.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/social-network-referrals-300x144.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Even better, you can see how much revenue that social media traffic is earning you by going to <strong>Acquisition  Social  Overview</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133569\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/social-overview.png\" alt=\"social overview\" width=\"620\" height=\"298\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/social-overview.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/social-overview-300x144.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>In the screenshot above, you can see the portion of conversions that came from social media referrals. Facebook makes up the biggest portion of social referrals by far in the example above, which means their Facebook content marketing ROI is in good shape. If they&#8217;d been pouring resources into marketing on Facebook but not seeing a lot of conversions in this screen, they&#8217;d know that their marketing was not worth the investment.</p>\n<p>Overall, however, if they&#8217;re focusing on social content marketing of any kind, they aren&#8217;t seeing any benefit from it, according to these analytics.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Use Buzzsumo to Measure Content Success</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://buzzsumo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Buzzsumo</a> is another great tool for measuring content marketing success, by tracking social media shares.</p>\n<p>If people are sharing your content, that means they find it valuable, and it also expands its potential reach, so you can get even more leads and sales.</p>\n<p>Just type the URL of a piece of content to see how many shares it&#8217;s got.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133570\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/buzzsumo-content-analyzer.png\" alt=\"buzzsumo content analyzer\" width=\"620\" height=\"214\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/buzzsumo-content-analyzer.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/buzzsumo-content-analyzer-300x104.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If people are sharing your content on the social networks that are most important to you, then it&#8217;ll enhance your reputation, drive traffic, bring in leads and, potentially, help you make sales, so it&#8217;s important to do this kind of analysis.</p>\n<h3>Does Your Content Show Up in Search Results?</h3>\n<p>If you&#8217;re measuring content marketing ROI, another important metric to keep track of is how well your content performs in search.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s because <a href=\"https://moz.com/blog/google-organic-click-through-rates-in-2014\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">more people click on the top search results</a>, and more clicks equal more traffic, and more potential leads and sales.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cmseo\">6. SEO Success</h3>\n<p>Search engine optimization (SEO) is the practice of increasing your website traffic by getting your web pages to rank higher in search engine results and it is so important.</p>\n<p>To gauge SEO performance, you&#8217;ll need to check that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your content ranks well for your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/keyword-research-101-how-to-choose-the-right-terms-for-google/\">target keywords</a>.</li>\n<li>You&#8217;re <a href=\"https://moz.com/blog/how-to-appear-in-googles-answer-boxes-whiteboard-friday\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">appearing in answer boxes</a> for relevant terms.</li>\n<li>Your domain authority is high (this happens when high authority sites link to you)</li>\n<li>You&#8217;re getting more inbound links.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If all these things are true, your content will reach more people, and you&#8217;ll get more leads and sales as a result.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s one way to analyze SEO performance for your content:</p>\n<p>First, open an incognito or private window in your browser, and search for one of the key terms that you&#8217;d like people to use to find your site. In this example, we searched for &#8220;page-level targeting,&#8221; one of OptinMonster&#8217;s key features.</p>\n<p>Where does your content show up in the results? If it&#8217;s in the top 3, you can be pretty sure you&#8217;ll get some traffic from it. And more traffic means more leads and more sales, so this is a great way to get a quick snapshot of how your content is doing.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133571\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-search-example.png\" alt=\"content marketing roi search example\" width=\"594\" height=\"700\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-search-example.png 594w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-search-example-255x300.png 255w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also use Moz&#8217;s <a href=\"https://moz.com/link-explorer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Link Explorer</a> to find your domain authority and page authority, and the domain and page authority of inbound links.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133572\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/moz-link-explorer.png\" alt=\"moz\'s link explorer\" width=\"620\" height=\"369\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/moz-link-explorer.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/moz-link-explorer-300x179.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Just type the URL into the search box, hit enter, and you&#8217;ll get an immediate snapshot. This tells you two things:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>High domain authority and page authority lets you know your content is seen as authoritative and will rank well in search results.</li>\n<li>Those same metrics for inbound links shows that respected sites are linking to your content, which increases your site&#8217;s authority even further.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We&#8217;ll talk more about what this means in the next tip.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cmauthority\">7. Exposure and Authority</h3>\n<p>Most of the metrics we&#8217;ve mentioned have been online <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/8-web-metrics-you-need-to-track-to-improve-conversion/\">website metrics</a>, but exposure and authority happen both online AND offline.</p>\n<p>The more people see you as an authority, the more they will want to share and link to your content, increasing its reach, and improving the potential to generate leads and sales.</p>\n<p>To track this, search for a topic keyword as described above and see where your site appears. For example, if you search for &#8220;content marketing,&#8221; the top result is the Content Marketing Institute.</p>\n<p>The Moz metrics we mentioned in Step 6 are a good indicator of online authority because you can measure your online authority and high-quality citations and track how these increase over time.</p>\n<p>Offline, you can assess your exposure and authority by checking that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You&#8217;re being invited to participate in industry events or expert roundups. Track this by monitoring the number of invitations you get. Easy peasy.</li>\n<li>You&#8217;re getting coverage from respected media outlets, including radio and television. Create a spreadsheet to track offline media mentions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These exposure and authority metrics are markers of content marketing success because they allow your content to reach an even wider audience, potentially sending more visitors to your site.</p>\n<p>When people start recognizing your brand and seeing you as an authority, that&#8217;ll lead to an increase in business referrals, leads, and sales, improving content marketing ROI.</p>\n<p>There you have it7 key content marketing metrics!</p>\n<p>Remember, <strong>you don&#8217;t need to track every single metric above</strong>. In fact, we recommend that you don&#8217;t.</p>\n<p>Trying to track too many metrics at once can be counterproductive and lead to &#8220;analysis paralysis.&#8221; Instead, start each new content marketing project or campaign by choosing a few relevant metrics to set concrete goals for. Then your ROI will be easy to track and you&#8217;ll know exactly what success looks like.</p>\n<p>Now that you know how to measure your content marketing ROI, it&#8217;s time to get started on creating more content. You can start with some <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/keyword-research-101-how-to-choose-the-right-terms-for-google/\">keyword research</a>, which is a good starting point for creating not just <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/50-blog-post-ideas-that-you-can-write-about-today/\">blog posts</a>, but <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/mistakes-to-avoid-when-writing-your-first-ebook/\">ebooks</a>, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-write-an-epic-case-study-that-wins-more-business/\">case studies</a>, and other <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/9-lead-magnets-to-increase-subscribers/\">lead magnets</a>.</p>\n<p>And, for even more content marketing success, avoid these <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/content-marketing-mistakes-experts-regret/\">content marketing mistakes</a> that even the experts make.</p>\n<p>Want more awesome advice like this? Follow us on <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/Optinmonster?sub_confirmation=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">YouTube</a>,<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/optinmonster\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a>, and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/optinmonster\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a>!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-measure-content-marketing-roi-metrics/\">How to Measure Your Content Marketing ROI + 7 Metrics That Matter</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-measure-content-marketing-roi-metrics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"How To Create a Contact Form for WordPress in 5 Easy Steps\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 08 Jul 2019 13:00:19 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"contact form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"contact form plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"how to\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"how to create a contact form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"wpforms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://optinmonster.com/?p=133503\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:568:\"<p>Contact forms are a wonderful way to let your visitors get in touch with you and keep your site looking professional. But, do you know how to create a contact form quickly and easily, without design and coding skills? Dont worry, you will! In this article, well show you how to create a contact form [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form/\">How To Create a Contact Form for WordPress in 5 Easy Steps</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Jacinda Santora\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17627:\"<p>Contact forms are a wonderful way to let your visitors get in touch with you and keep your site looking professional. But, do you know how to create a contact form quickly and easily, without design and coding skills?</p>\n<p>Dont worry, you will!</p>\n<p>In this article, well show you how to create a contact form in WordPress in 5 easy steps.</p>\n<h3>Why do You Need a Contact Form?</h3>\n<p>Right now, you may be sitting there asking, Do I really need to add a contact form to my website? I have my email address on there; isnt that enough?</p>\n<p>Lets take a minute to get those questions answered, okay?</p>\n<p>In short, <strong>yes, you really need a contact form on your website</strong>. Here are <strong>4 excellent reason</strong>s why:</p>\n<p><strong>1. Offers Spam Protection.</strong> Spambots regularly scrape websites for email addresses, so when you put your email address on your website, youre going to start getting a lot of spam emails. With a contact form, however, you can expect to get rid of <strong>almost all</strong> spam emails.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133510\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/spam-protection.png\" alt=\"spam protection\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/spam-protection.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/spam-protection-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>2. Saves Time.</strong> A contact form is timesaving for both you and your site visitors. For starters, the form is right on your site, ready for visitors to enter their contact info and message and send immediately. You can deliver an immediate confirmation or <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/anatomy-of-the-perfect-thank-you-page/\">thank you message</a>, letting them know what are the next steps, and you dont have to enter their contact info into your CRM, because its already there!</p>\n<p><strong>3. Keeps Information Organized.</strong> As we hinted at above, you wont be stuck entering contact details manually into your CRM; with a contact form, the information will come through already organized the way you want it. You control the information by only adding the fields you want to collect, cutting down on the back and forth between you and a potential customer.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133511\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/keeps-information-organized.png\" alt=\"keep information organized\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/keeps-information-organized.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/keeps-information-organized-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>4. Lead Generation.</strong> You probably already know that OptinMonster is the best lead generation software available, but what if you want to collect more detail from your leads up front When you combine the awesome lead generation power of OptinMonster with the right contact form plugin, you can <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/beginners-guide-to-conversion-rate-optimization/\">use your contact form to increase your conversions</a>.</p>\n<p>Now that you know the importance of including a contact form on your WordPress site, how do you choose the best plugin to make the process as easy as drag, drop, done?</p>\n<p>Weve got you covered on that, too.</p>\n<h3>Choosing the Best Contact Form Plugin</h3>\n<p>Weve taken the time to review and handpick the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins/\">best contact form plugins</a> for you. You can simply choose one from our curated list.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-122545\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins.png\" alt=\"best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>For this tutorial, weve chosen <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPForms</a> because its the <strong>best contact form plugin</strong> for WordPress.</p>\n<p>There are quite a few free and paid WordPress contact form plugins out there, but we use WPForms on the OptinMonster site and believe that its hands down the best option out there.</p>\n<p>You can use WPForms Lite to create a simple contact form if you need a free option. And, when youre ready for more advanced features, upgrade to WPForms Pro.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133514\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms.png\" alt=\"wpforms logo\" width=\"620\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>With WPForms Pro you get access to survey reports, user registration forms, payment forms, post submission forms, smart conditional logic, conversational forms, and a lot moreall without touching any code.</p>\n<p>Of course, both WPForms Lite and WPForms Pro come with the intuitive drag and drop form builder to make building awesome forms a breeze.</p>\n<h3>How to Create a Contact Form Using WPForms</h3>\n<p>To get started with WPForms, youll need to install and activate the WPForms plugin. Check out the step by step guide on <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a plugin in WordPress</a> for more details.</p>\n<h3>Step 1. Create a Simple Contact Form</h3>\n<p>Once you have your plugin installed, go to <strong>WPForms  Add New</strong>from your WordPress dashboard to create a new form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-133516 size-full\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-add-new.png\" alt=\"how to create a contact form with wpforms\" width=\"620\" height=\"272\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-add-new.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-add-new-300x132.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Name your form and select the <strong>Simple Contact Form template</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133517\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/name-select-simple-contact-form.png\" alt=\"name your form and select the simple contact form template\" width=\"620\" height=\"342\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/name-select-simple-contact-form.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/name-select-simple-contact-form-300x165.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You can add more fields to your contact form by dragging them from the left-hand panel to the right-hand panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133519\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-fields-to-form.gif\" alt=\"add form fields\" width=\"620\" height=\"390\" /></p>\n<p>Next, click on a field in the right-hand panel to make changes to that field using the form field options.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133520\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/form-field-options.png\" alt=\"form field options\" width=\"620\" height=\"433\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/form-field-options.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/form-field-options-300x210.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also click on a form field and drag it to rearrange the order on your contact form.</p>\n<p>When youre happy with the look of your form, click <strong>Save</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Step 2. Configure Your General Form Settings</h3>\n<p>Go to <strong>Settings  General</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133521\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/general-contact-form-settings.png\" alt=\"general contact form settings\" width=\"620\" height=\"471\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/general-contact-form-settings.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/general-contact-form-settings-300x228.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Here you can configure a number of things about your form:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Form Name.</strong> Choose a different name for your form, if youd like.</li>\n<li><strong>Form Description.</strong> Give your form a description.</li>\n<li><strong>Submit Button Text.</strong> Change the copy on the submit button.</li>\n<li><strong>Spam Prevention.</strong> You can enable the honeypot feature to keep spambots from submitting forms. This feature is automatically enabled on all WordPress forms, but if you use another form of spam prevention, unclick this option.</li>\n<li><strong>GDPR Enhancements.</strong> You can disable the storing of entry information and user details, like IP addresses and user agents, an effort to comply with <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/gdpr/\">GDPR requirements</a>. In addition, check out the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-gdpr-agreement-field-to-your-sites-forms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPForms instructions</a> on how to add a GDPR agreement field to your simple contact form.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When youre done, click <strong>Save</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Step 3. Configure Your Contact Form Notifications</h3>\n<p>Want to receive a notification whenever someone submits a contact form on your site? You can do that by going to<strong>Settings  Notifications</strong>.</p>\n<p>But, receiving notifications on form submission is actually the default setup, so unless you disable it or want to change it, youll get a notification about submitted contact forms and don&#8217;t have to do anything here.<img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f600.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>To turn off contact form submissions, simply select<strong>Off</strong> from the<strong>Notifications</strong> dropdown.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133522\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/turn-contact-form-submissions-off.png\" alt=\"turn contact form submissions off\" width=\"620\" height=\"232\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/turn-contact-form-submissions-off.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/turn-contact-form-submissions-off-300x112.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>Step 4. Configure Your Contact Form Confirmations</h3>\n<p>Form confirmations are messages that show up to site visitors when they submit a contact form on your website. They let people know that their form has been processed and give you the chance to let them know what their next steps should be.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133527\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/form-confirmation-page.png\" alt=\"form confirmation page\" width=\"620\" height=\"142\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/form-confirmation-page.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/form-confirmation-page-300x69.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>WPForms has 3 confirmation types to choose from:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Message.</strong> This is the default confirmation type and shows when a site visitor submits a contact form. Its a simple message confirmation that lets them know their form was processed.</li>\n<li><strong>Show Page.</strong> This confirmation type takes site visitors to a specific thank you page on your site. Be sure to check out our article on <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/11-ways-to-increase-conversion-rates-on-your-thank-you-pages/\">ways to increase conversion rates on your thank you pages</a> to make the most of this value but often overlooked page.</li>\n<li><strong>Go to URL (Redirect).</strong> The redirect option is used when you want to send site visitors to a different website.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Heres how to set up a form confirmation in WPForms to customize the message visitors see when they submit a contact form.</p>\n<p>First, click on the <strong>Confirmation tab</strong> in the Form Editor under <strong>Settings</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133528\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-confirmation-message.png\" alt=\"wpforms confirmation messages\" width=\"620\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-confirmation-message.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-confirmation-message-300x136.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, choose the type of confirmation type you want to create. For this example, well select <strong>Message</strong> since its the most popular.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133529\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-choose-confirmation-type.png\" alt=\"choose confirmation type\" width=\"620\" height=\"524\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-choose-confirmation-type.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-choose-confirmation-type-300x254.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, edit the confirmation message and click <strong>Save</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Step 5. Add Your Contact Form to Your Website</h3>\n<p>Now that youve created your simple contact form, its time to add it to your WordPress website.</p>\n<p>WPForms lets you add your forms in many locations on your websites, like blog posts, pages, and sidebar widgets. Most people add forms to posts or pages, so well go with that option.</p>\n<p>Create a new post or page in WordPress (or choose an existing post or page you want to add your form to) and click on the <strong>Add Form button</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133530\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-add-to-post.gif\" alt=\"add wpforms form to a new wordpress post\" width=\"620\" height=\"498\" /></p>\n<p>Next, select your contact form in the modal popup and click <strong>Add Form</strong>.</p>\n<p>Then, <strong>publish</strong> your post or page and your contact form will show up on your website!</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133532\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-example-on-site.png\" alt=\"wpforms example on live site\" width=\"620\" height=\"470\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-example-on-site.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-example-on-site-300x227.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>Track Your WordPress Contact Form Conversions</h3>\n<p>Even though its easy, you want to know how your forms are performing, right? That&#8217;s why its important to track form analytics just as you would other data on your site.</p>\n<p>You can do that with <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights</a>, a user-friendly tool that lets you painlessly harness the massive power of Google Analytics in just a few clickswithout having to touch a single line of code.</p>\n<p>Just install and activate <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/forms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights Forms</a>, and the plugin will start tracking your forms automatically.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133533\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Forms-Report-MonsterInsights.png\" alt=\"forms report from monsterinsights\" width=\"620\" height=\"479\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Forms-Report-MonsterInsights.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Forms-Report-MonsterInsights-300x232.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Youll be able to track the total number of views and conversions your forms are triggering as well as your form conversion rates. In addition, you can find out which form is collecting the most submissions.</p>\n<p>MonsterInsights and the powerful forms tracking addon provide the insight you need to make sure your forms are performing the way you want.</p>\n<p>Thats it! Youve just learned how to create a contact form for your WordPress site using WPForms. Plus, you can track its success with MonsterInsights. Now that youre a WPForms whiz, why not try your hand at <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-ways-to-collect-customer-feedback/\">creating a customer feedback form</a>?</p>\n<p>And dont forget that OptinMonster + WPForms is conversion magic. <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing/\">Get started with OptinMonster RIGHT NOW.</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form/\">How To Create a Contact Form for WordPress in 5 Easy Steps</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"Top 8 Best Google Analytics Plugins for WordPress (Expert Pick)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://optinmonster.com/best-google-analytics-plugins/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://optinmonster.com/best-google-analytics-plugins/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 05 Jul 2019 12:55:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"best google analytics plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"ga plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"google analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"google analytics plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"wordpress plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"wordpress plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://optinmonster.com/?p=133433\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:603:\"<p>What would happen if your car didn&#8217;t come with a dashboard? No way of knowing how fast you&#8217;re going, no lights to tell you when something is happening that shouldn&#8217;t be, and nothing to tell you where you should be focusing your attention. Scary, right? No way you&#8217;d drive a car without analytics! Analytics are [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-google-analytics-plugins/\">Top 8 Best Google Analytics Plugins for WordPress (Expert Pick)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Jacinda Santora\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26364:\"<p>What would happen if your car didn&#8217;t come with a dashboard?</p>\n<p>No way of knowing how fast you&#8217;re going, no lights to tell you when something is happening that shouldn&#8217;t be, and nothing to tell you where you should be focusing your attention.</p>\n<p>Scary, right? No way you&#8217;d drive a car without analytics!</p>\n<p>Analytics are important for your website, too. In this article, we&#8217;ve hand-picked the best Google Analytics plugins for WordPress users. We&#8217;ll take you through the pros and cons of each and help you choose the best Google Analytics plugin for your needs.</p>\n<h3>What Is Google Analytics?</h3>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133457\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-landing.png\" alt=\"google analytics home page\" width=\"620\" height=\"286\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-landing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-landing-300x138.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Google Analytics a free analytics solution that can be easily installed in WordPress using the plugins included in this article. You can also install it to any website by adding the code directly.</p>\n<p>You can use Google Analytics on a single site or install it on multiple websites and view all your reports under one dashboard using a single code.</p>\n<p>Google Analytics shows you the number of visitors to your site and has advanced reports you can use to track links, perform <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ab-testing-best-practices/\">A/B testing</a>, track <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-engage-website-visitors/\">user engagement</a>, get real-time traffic insights, and even more.</p>\n<p>So, now that you know all about Google Analytics, you&#8217;re probably wondering, &#8220;Do I really need a Google Analytics plugin?&#8221; or &#8220;How can I find the best Google Analytics plugin?&#8221;</p>\n<p>Good thing you&#8217;re here because we&#8217;re covering both of those right here in this very article. Keep reading!</p>\n<h3>Why Do You Need a Google Analytics Plugin?</h3>\n<p>Web analytics help you get detailed insights on your site visitors which can help you make informed, data-driven decisions that will grow your business.</p>\n<p>With a Google Analytics plugin, you&#8217;ll be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Know where your referral traffic comes from.</strong> When you know where your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-to-use-optinmonsters-referral-detection-for-advanced-lead-targeting/\">referral traffic</a> is coming from, you know where to invest your marketing dollars.</li>\n<li><strong>Segment your audience.</strong> You can create specific campaigns to target specific <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/university/guides/50-smart-ways-to-segment-your-email-list/\">segments of your audience</a> when you know more about who your audience is.</li>\n<li><strong>Track the effectiveness of your campaigns.</strong> Keep track of how your campaigns are performing with advanced reporting.</li>\n<li><strong>Create and track conversion goals.</strong> Google Analytics allows you to create and track <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/optinmonster-event-goals-google-analytics/\">custom conversion goals</a> so you can track each stage in the <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/roadmap-to-capturing-leads-throughout-the-customer-journey/\">customer journey</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Analyze and improve your content marketing.</strong> With Google Analytics, you can find out what <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/keyword-research-101-how-to-choose-the-right-terms-for-google/\">keywords you&#8217;re ranking for</a> and what <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/content-marketing-guide/\">content is working</a> for you.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And that&#8217;s just the beginning of what you can do with an analytics plugin on your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>Can you use Google Analytics without a plugin? Yes. Does a plugin make it a billion times easier? YES.</p>\n<p>You can probably see why we&#8217;re so excited about sharing these plugins with you, so let&#8217;s dive into our picks for the <strong>best Google Analytics plugins for WordPress</strong>!</p>\n<h3>1. <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133439\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-landing-2.png\" alt=\"grow your business with confidence with monsterinsights\" width=\"620\" height=\"298\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-landing-2.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-landing-2-300x144.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>With a staggering 2+ million active installations, MonsterInsights is the most popular Google Analytics plugin for WordPress, and there&#8217;s a reason it tops many &#8220;best Google Analytics plugins&#8221; lists.</p>\n<p>The MonsterInsights plugin makes it just about effortless to set up even the most <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-optinmonster-uses-google-analytics-to-measure-conversion-analytics/\">advanced Google Analytics features</a> in WordPress with just a few clicks. No coding necessary and no developers needed.</p>\n<p>With the built-in Google Analytics dashboard, you don&#8217;t even have to leave WordPress to get useful visitor information. Just access the MonsterInsights dashboard right from WordPress to access all the analytics you need.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133458\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-wordpress-dashboard.png\" alt=\"monsterinsights wordpress dashboard\" width=\"620\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-wordpress-dashboard.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-wordpress-dashboard-300x143.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The plugin also comes with several addons that extend the functionality of the plugin and make it even more useful.</p>\n<p>Google Analytics Enhanced eCommerce tracking for WooCommerce, Easy Digital Downloads, and MemberPress lets you track things like <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/18-ways-increasing-conversions-throughout-your-sales-funnel/\">conversion rate</a>, transactions, and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/increase-your-average-order-value/\">average order value</a> with a single click.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133459\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-ecommerce-addon.png\" alt=\"monsterinsights ecommerce addon\" width=\"620\" height=\"434\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-ecommerce-addon.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-ecommerce-addon-300x210.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The EU Compliance addon makes it easy to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Anonymize IP in Google Analytics</li>\n<li>Disable the Demographics and Interest Reports for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/google-display-retargeting-ads/\">Remarketing</a> and Advertising</li>\n<li>Disable UserID and author name tracking</li>\n<li>Integrate with Cookie Notice and CookieBot plugins to collect user consent before tracking</li>\n<li>Integrate with Google AMP Consent Box before enable tracking</li>\n<li>Integrate with Google Analytics Chrome browser opt-out extension and built-in cookie opt-out system</li>\n<li>Offer Easy Opt Out link for Google Analytics tracking</li>\n</ul>\n<p>MonsterInsights also comes with a Forms addon that lets you easily track form views, submissions, and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins/\">form conversion rates</a>!</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133461\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-custom-dimensions.png\" alt=\"monsterinsights custom dimensions\" width=\"620\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-custom-dimensions.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-custom-dimensions-300x249.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Other Features You&#8217;ll Love:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Google Analytics universal tracking, so you can track your users across devices and platforms</li>\n<li>1-click Google Analytics integration with <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/7-steps-to-optimize-your-facebook-ads-for-conversions/\">Facebook Instant Articles</a></li>\n<li>MonsterInsights Ads tracking addon so publishers can easily track the performance of their <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/wordpress-link-tracking-plugins/\">Google AdSense Ads</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/wordpress-link-tracking-plugins/\">Affiliate link tracking</a> makes it easy for bloggers and affiliate marketers to track their affiliate links</li>\n<li>MonsterInsights custom Google analytics event tracking feature lets you easily add outbound-link tracking, file downloads tracking, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-the-perfect-call-to-action/\">call-to-action button</a> tracking, hashmark tracking, telephone link tracking, and more</li>\n<li>Custom Dimensions addonlets you use Google Analytics custom dimensions to generate helpful WordPress stats for things like author, SEO score, and focus keyword tracking</li>\n<li>Multisite support</li>\n<li>Built-in permissions so you can control who has access to view the Google Analytics dashboard</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133460\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-user-roles.png\" alt=\"monsterinsights user roles\" width=\"620\" height=\"521\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-user-roles.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsights-user-roles-300x252.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights is simple to use but comes packed with advanced features that make it a great choice for beginners and seasoned marketers alike.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Get started with MonsterInsights today!</a></p>\n<h3>2. <a href=\"https://exactmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ExactMetrics</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://exactmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133440\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/exactmetrics-landing.png\" alt=\"exactmetrics home page\" width=\"620\" height=\"310\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/exactmetrics-landing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/exactmetrics-landing-300x150.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Next up in our list of the best Google Analytics plugins for WordPress is ExactMetrics.</p>\n<p>ExactMetrics is one of the top free Google Analytics plugins for WordPress and has over 1 million active installs.</p>\n<p>This plugin allows users to easily install the latest Google Analytics tracking code to view beautiful Google Analytics reports directly in their WordPress admin area. These reports include important information like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sessions and pagviews</li>\n<li>Organic searches</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/4-ways-to-reduce-your-bounce-rate-with-optinmonster/\">Bounce rates</a></li>\n<li>Referrers</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-404-page-examples/\">404 errors</a></li>\n<li>Traffic channels</li>\n<li>And more&#8230;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133467\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/exactmetrics-dashboard.png\" alt=\"exactmetrics dashboard\" width=\"620\" height=\"349\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/exactmetrics-dashboard.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/exactmetrics-dashboard-300x169.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Additionally, the Google Analytics tracking code is fully customizable which allows for advanced data collection like events (downloads, page scrolling length, etc.) and custom dimensions (author, publication year, etc.).</p>\n<p>As we already mentioned, ExactMetrics is free! It&#8217;s also well-supported.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://exactmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Give ExactMetrics a try today!</a></p>\n<h3>3. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-analytify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Analytify</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-analytify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133441\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/analytify-landing.png\" alt=\"analytify home page\" width=\"620\" height=\"185\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/analytify-landing.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/analytify-landing-300x90.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Analytify rounds out the top 3 in our list of best Google Analytics plugins for WordPress. It offers super easy installation and just like MonsterInsights, lets you view your Google Analytics reports right inside your WordPress admin area.</p>\n<p>You can also get page-level analytics for every page and post, as well as detailed stats for your custom post types, like portfolio, galleries, and testimonials.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133469\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/analytify-post-page-level-analytics.png\" alt=\"analytify post page-level analytics\" width=\"620\" height=\"454\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/analytify-post-page-level-analytics.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/analytify-post-page-level-analytics-300x220.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>To extend its functionality, Analytify includes a few addons. Here are our favorites:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>eCommerce tracking for WooCommerce and Easy Digital Downloads.</strong> These addons let you track sales, transactions, and revenues and display the stats in an easy-to-understand way.</li>\n<li><strong>Email Notifications.</strong> If you want your Google Analytics reports sent to your (or your clients) in a beautiful, HTML email format, this is the addon you need.</li>\n<li><strong>Goals.</strong> This addon makes it easy to create and showcase goals and goal completion to your clients, right from your WordPress dashboard.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There&#8217;s also a Campaigns addon totrack individual campaigns using <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/docs/how-to-target-optins-to-your-pay-per-click-campaigns/\">UTM (Urchin Tracking Module)</a> parameters.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-analytify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with Analytify today!</a></p>\n<h3>4. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/enhanced-e-commerce-for-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics Plugin</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/enhanced-e-commerce-for-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133442\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-woocommerce.png\" alt=\"Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"277\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-woocommerce.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-woocommerce-300x134.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for a Google Analytics plugin to track your WooCommerce store, this free WordPress plugin might just be the plugin for you.</p>\n<p>Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics Plugin uses the eCommerce tracking feature of Google Analytics to help you <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-optimization-guide/\">optimize your online store</a> based on the data collected from visitor behavior. The plugin supports all the in-depth reporting the Google Analytics offers, as well as 4 new reports included in Enhanced eCommerce:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Shopping Behavior</li>\n<li>Checkout Behavior</li>\n<li>Product Performance</li>\n<li>Sales Performance</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This plugin also helps you capture a ton of site behavior that will help you understand <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/google-analytics-segments-and-optinmonster-campaigns/\">how visitors are browsing and shopping your site</a>.</p>\n<p>Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics Plugin does come with limitations, of course. For starters, it only supports simple products, highly customized stores, subscription products, shortcodes, or child themes.</p>\n<p>If none of those is a dealbreaker for you, Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics Plugin is a solidand freeGoogle Analytics plugin for WordPress that can give you the insight you need for your WooCommerce store.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/enhanced-e-commerce-for-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Give Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics Plugin a try today!</a></p>\n<h3>5. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wd-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Google Analytics by 10Web</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wd-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133443\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-10web.png\" alt=\"google analytics by 10web\" width=\"620\" height=\"201\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-10web.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/google-analytics-10web-300x97.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Google Analytics by 10Web is another easy-to-install plugin that lets you set and manage goals, create and use custom dimensions, and view Google Analytics reports from the comfort of your WordPress admin area.</p>\n<p>This plugin also integrates with Google Ads and Google AdSense to give you important data about your ad campaigns all in the same dashboard.</p>\n<p>Here are some of the other features you&#8217;re bound to enjoy:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>eCommerce reporting</li>\n<li>Goal management</li>\n<li>Custom reporting</li>\n<li>Alerts when metrics reach specified high or low points</li>\n<li>Share reports via automated email</li>\n<li>Export reports to CSV files</li>\n<li>Filter tracked data to exclude certain user types, locations, or IP addresses</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Google Analytics by 10Web also features outstanding customers support and vows to resolve your issue, should you have one, within 24 hours.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wd-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with Google Analytics by 10Web today!</a></p>\n<h3>6. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ga-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GA Google Analytics</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ga-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133472\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-google-analytics-plugin.png\" alt=\"ga google analytics plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"248\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-google-analytics-plugin.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ga-google-analytics-plugin-300x120.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Are you looking for a lightweight Google Analytics plugin that simply does the work of connecting your WordPress site to Google Analytics?</p>\n<p>GA Google Analytics isGDPR compliant and enables the Google Analytics tracking code on all the pages of your WordPress site. You can evendisable tracking of admin-level users so your data isn&#8217;t skewed by the people who are on your site for work-related reasons.</p>\n<p>As far as features go, however, that&#8217;s about it for this plugin. To get additional features, you&#8217;ll have to upgrade to the pro version of this plugin. This Google Analytics plugin is designed for simplicity and it delivers.</p>\n<p>To access your Google Analytics data and reports you&#8217;ll have to log in to your Google Analytics account.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ga-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Click here to get started with GA Google Analytics!</a></p>\n<h3>7. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WP Statistics</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133446\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wp-statistics-plugin.png\" alt=\"wp statistics plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"201\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wp-statistics-plugin.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wp-statistics-plugin-300x97.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WP Statistics is a free/freemium, easy-to-install WordPress analytics plugin that shows stats and simple graphs inside your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>You can track visitor data like IP address, referring site, browser, operating system, country, and city, as well as track redirects from search engines like Google, Yahoo, Bing, DuckDuckGo, and more.</p>\n<p>WP Statistics also supports WordPress roles and lets you set access levels to view and manage analytics. Additionally, you can export your analytics data to XML, CSV, or TSV files and WP Statistics also can send an email statistics summary with customizable text.</p>\n<p>A downside of this plugin is that it stores the data on your WordPress site. Over time, this may increase your backup size.</p>\n<p>Backup size not a problem? <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with WP Statistics today!</a></p>\n<h3>8. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-google-analytics-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WP Google Analytics Events</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-google-analytics-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-133448\" src=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wp-google-analytics-events.png\" alt=\"wp google analytics events plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"201\" srcset=\"https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wp-google-analytics-events.png 620w, https://optinmonster.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wp-google-analytics-events-300x97.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>This plugin makes it super easy to send events to Google Analytics when a visitor scrolls to a specific point of interest on your WordPress site or they click certain elements on your site, like buttons or Ajax submit formswith no coding required.</p>\n<p>Event tracking in Google Analytics is incredibly powerful and useful for understanding what your visitors do on your website. Here are just a few things you could do with the WP Google Analytics Events plugin:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Track in-page navigation</li>\n<li>Compare <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/which-color-button-converts-best/\">call-to-action button performance</a></li>\n<li>Understand what percentage of your visitors read to the end of a post</li>\n<li>Track <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-wordpress-form-builder-plugins/\">contact form conversions</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a fan of using videos in your posts, you should check out the premium version of the plugin that lets you create events to track video views, pauses, and completions. Pretty cool, right?</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s important to remember that this plugin is only for event tracking, so you&#8217;ll still need another option to track your site stats and demographics.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-google-analytics-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with WP Google Analytics Events today!</a></p>\n<h3>What Is the Best Google Analytics Plugin for WordPress?</h3>\n<p>That&#8217;s it for our top picks for best Google Analytics plugins, so now it&#8217;s time to pick a winner, right? Drumroll, please: </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights</a> is hands down the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It offers an incredible selection of features, is backed back an awesome team that works hard to keep the plugin updated and the software behind it constantly improving, and lets you do everything you need to do from the comfort of your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for the best free Google Analytics plugin for WordPress, we highly recommend <a href=\"https://exactmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ExactMetrics</a>.</p>\n<p>We hope this article about the best Google Analytics plugins was exactly what you were looking for! If you&#8217;re interested in learning more about Google Analytics, why notset up your Google Analytics account and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/google-analytics-101-how-to-track-your-conversions-step-by-step/\"><strong>start creating conversion goals</strong></a>?</p>\n<p>And, don&#8217;t forget that <strong>OptinMonster is the #1 conversion software in the world</strong>. Whatever your goals are, we get you there. <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/pricing\">Get started with OptinMonster today!</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-google-analytics-plugins/\">Top 8 Best Google Analytics Plugins for WordPress (Expert Pick)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://optinmonster.com\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"https://optinmonster.com/best-google-analytics-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:30:\"https://optinmonster.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:11:{s:6:\"server\";s:13:\"nginx/1.15.10\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Sun, 14 Jul 2019 05:03:31 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Sat, 13 Jul 2019 12:14:22 GMT\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"51107662d205265bdfc68a06f7cc204f\"\";s:12:\"x-robots-tag\";s:15:\"noindex, follow\";s:4:\"link\";a:2:{i:0;s:61:\"<https://optinmonster.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\"\";i:1;s:41:\"<https://optin.to/2jE9SDH>; rel=shortlink\";}s:9:\"x-backend\";s:22:\"awesomemotive-web4.com\";s:8:\"x-cached\";s:3:\"HIT\";s:13:\"x-proxy-cache\";s:3:\"HIT\";s:25:\"strict-transport-security\";s:13:\"max-age=86400\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20190712144711\";}', 'no');
